55
00:11:56.121 --> 00:11:58.825
WOMAN: Laurie! Laurie!

56
00:12:07.264 --> 00:12:09.396
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

57
00:12:13.875 --> 00:12:16.843
(BAND RESUMES PLAYING MUSIC)

58
00:12:19.177 --> 00:12:21.408
Mama!

59
00:12:21.443 --> 00:12:24.048
Oh! Mama!

60
00:12:24.083 --> 00:12:25.951
(SIGHS)

61
00:12:25.986 --> 00:12:27.282
Look who's here.

62
00:12:27.317 --> 00:12:28.855
Ah! Father Carmelo.
Connie. how are you?

63
00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:30.252
This is
Father Carmelo.

64
00:12:30.287 --> 00:12:32.122
I'm Merle Johnson.
Pleased to meet you.

65
00:12:34.093 --> 00:12:36.555
Mama!

66
00:12:36.590 --> 00:12:38.260
Here I am.

67
00:12:38.295 --> 00:12:41.032
Constanzia.<i> finalmente.</i>
after one week?

68
00:12:41.067 --> 00:12:45.168
I sent the car to the airport
last week to pick you up.
Oh.

69
00:12:45.203 --> 00:12:48.402
It was chaos.
Anyway. here I am.
just one week late.

70
00:12:48.437 --> 00:12:51.240
Oh!
This is for my mama!

71
00:12:51.275 --> 00:12:53.506
What is this?
You remember
Merle don't you?

72
00:12:53.541 --> 00:12:57.279
Hello. Mama.
Hello. How are you?
Thank you.

73
00:12:57.314 --> 00:12:59.116
Where's Michael?
I've got to talk to him

74
00:12:59.151 --> 00:13:01.855
and get a few things straight
and I can't wait on line.

75
00:13:03.122 --> 00:13:05.419
You go see your
children first.

76
00:13:05.454 --> 00:13:09.027
And then you worry
about waiting on line
to see your brother.

77
00:13:09.062 --> 00:13:10.897
Like everybody else.

78
00:13:10.932 --> 00:13:14.296
(CEREMONIAL MUSIC PLAYING)

79
00:13:15.970 --> 00:13:17.937
CONDUCTOR ON MICROPHONE:
<i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

80
00:13:17.972 --> 00:13:20.236
CICCI: Frank. wake up.

81
00:13:20.271 --> 00:13:22.502
CONDUCTOR:<i> A most</i>
<i>distinguished guest would</i>
<i>like to say a few words.</i>

82
00:13:22.537 --> 00:13:27.012
<i>Would you please welcome</i>
<i>Senator Pat Geary</i>
<i>of the State of Nevada.</i>

83
00:13:27.047 --> 00:13:29.047
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)
<i>And there is Mrs. Geary.</i>

84
00:13:40.093 --> 00:13:42.357
GEARY:<i> Thank you</i>
<i>very much.</i>
<i>ladies and gentlemen.</i>

85
00:13:42.392 --> 00:13:45.591
<i>This is a very.</i>
<i>very happy day</i>

86
00:13:45.626 --> 00:13:49.562
<i>for me and. uh. my wife</i>
<i>Mrs. Geary.</i>

87
00:13:49.597 --> 00:13:53.005
<i>We see Nevada</i>
<i>far too seldom.</i>

88
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:55.106
<i>But particularly today</i>
<i>when we can...</i>

89
00:13:55.141 --> 00:13:58.076
<i>We can join</i>
<i>with old friends.</i>
<i>we can make new friends</i>

90
00:13:58.111 --> 00:14:02.608
<i>and we help celebrate</i>
<i>a young man's</i>
<i>first Communion.</i>

91
00:14:02.643 --> 00:14:05.611
<i>And also to thank</i>
<i>that boy's family</i>

92
00:14:05.646 --> 00:14:09.582
<i>for a magnificent</i>
<i>contribution to the State.</i>

93
00:14:09.617 --> 00:14:11.617
<i>I have here</i>
<i>in my hand a check</i>

94
00:14:13.159 --> 00:14:15.522
<i>made out to</i>
<i>the university</i>

95
00:14:15.557 --> 00:14:19.427
<i>and it is</i>
<i>a magnificent endowment</i>
<i>in the name of</i>

96
00:14:19.462 --> 00:14:21.935
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)
<i>Uh...</i>

97
00:14:21.970 --> 00:14:25.532
(MISPRONOUNCING)
<i>Anthony Vito Corleone.</i>

98
00:14:25.567 --> 00:14:29.008
<i>And the check is signed by</i>
<i>that young man's parents</i>

99
00:14:29.043 --> 00:14:31.439
<i>whom I think</i>
<i>we should recognize.</i>

100
00:14:31.474 --> 00:14:35.047
<i>Mike. Pat. uh. Kay.</i>
<i>stand up. please.</i>

101
00:14:35.082 --> 00:14:36.279
<i>Let the folks see you!</i>

102
00:14:36.314 --> 00:14:38.380
<i>Folks. I want you</i>
<i>to join with me</i>

103
00:14:38.415 --> 00:14:41.350
<i>in giving a real</i>
<i>Nevada "Thank you"</i>
<i>(DRUMROLL)</i>

104
00:14:41.385 --> 00:14:44.254
<i>to Mr. and Mrs.</i>
<i>Michael Corleone!</i>

105
00:14:45.389 --> 00:14:47.224
(INAUDIBLE)

106
00:14:50.130 --> 00:14:53.296
<i>We also have. as a special</i>
<i>added attraction.</i>

107
00:14:53.331 --> 00:14:55.496
<i>the Sierra Boys Choir</i>

108
00:14:55.531 --> 00:15:02.041
<i>who have chosen</i>
<i>a certain special song</i>
<i>and a special arrangement</i>

109
00:15:02.076 --> 00:15:06.210
<i>to honor their host.</i>
<i>Mr. Michael Corleone.</i>

110
00:15:06.245 --> 00:15:07.376
<i>Boys.</i>

111
00:15:09.578 --> 00:15:11.710
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

112
00:15:16.057 --> 00:15:19.520
(CHOIR SINGING)

113
00:15:24.296 --> 00:15:26.494
PHOTOGRAPHER: The plaque.

114
00:15:26.529 --> 00:15:28.265
Okay. fellows.
did you get that one?

115
00:15:30.038 --> 00:15:32.236
Okay. that's good.

116
00:15:32.271 --> 00:15:35.107
Now. Senator.
just you and Mrs. Corleone.

117
00:15:57.692 --> 00:16:01.034
This is my lawyer Tom Hagen.
Senator Geary.

118
00:16:01.069 --> 00:16:04.235
He's the one who arranged
this whole thing through
your man Turnbull.

119
00:16:04.270 --> 00:16:05.698
Yes. yes.

120
00:16:05.733 --> 00:16:07.370
Sit down.

121
00:16:10.474 --> 00:16:13.739
Well. I was under
the impression that
you and I would talk alone.

122
00:16:15.446 --> 00:16:18.348
I trust these men
with my life. Senator.

123
00:16:18.383 --> 00:16:21.318
If I were to ask
them to leave.
it would be an insult.

124
00:16:21.353 --> 00:16:24.156
Well. it's perfectly
all right with me

125
00:16:24.191 --> 00:16:29.194
but I am a blunt man
and I intend to speak
very frankly to you.

126
00:16:29.229 --> 00:16:31.229
Maybe more frankly

127
00:16:31.264 --> 00:16:34.595
than anyone in my position
has ever talked to you before.

128
00:16:34.630 --> 00:16:37.730
The Corleone family
has done well in Nevada.

129
00:16:37.765 --> 00:16:43.109
You own. or control.
two major hotels in Vegas

130
00:16:43.144 --> 00:16:45.441
and one in Reno.

131
00:16:45.476 --> 00:16:47.608
The licenses were
grandfathered in.

132
00:16:47.643 --> 00:16:51.249
so there was no problem
with the Gaming Commission.

133
00:16:53.220 --> 00:16:56.221
Now my sources tell me

134
00:16:56.256 --> 00:17:00.357
that you plan
to make a move
against the Tropigala.

135
00:17:00.392 --> 00:17:02.293
They tell me
that within a week.

136
00:17:02.328 --> 00:17:04.856
you're going to
move Klingman out.

137
00:17:04.891 --> 00:17:07.265
That's quite an expansion.

138
00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:11.137
However. it will
leave you with one little
technical problem.

139
00:17:11.172 --> 00:17:13.766
(GULPS)

140
00:17:13.801 --> 00:17:16.703
The license will still be
in Klingman's name.

141
00:17:17.838 --> 00:17:19.673
Turnbull is
a good man.

142
00:17:19.708 --> 00:17:22.544
Yeah. well. let's cut out
the bullshit.

143
00:17:22.579 --> 00:17:25.745
I don't want to spend
more time here
than I have to.

144
00:17:25.780 --> 00:17:28.352
You can have
the license.

145
00:17:28.387 --> 00:17:31.322
The price is
250.000 dollars.

146
00:17:31.357 --> 00:17:34.160
Plus a monthly payment
of five percent of the gross

147
00:17:34.195 --> 00:17:36.888
of all four hotels. Mr.. uh.

148
00:17:36.923 --> 00:17:38.527
(EMPHASIZES ITALIAN
PRONUNCIATION) Corleone.

149
00:17:42.236 --> 00:17:44.632
Now the price
for the license

150
00:17:44.667 --> 00:17:47.239
is less than
$20.000. right?

151
00:17:47.274 --> 00:17:49.637
GEARY: That's right.

152
00:17:49.672 --> 00:17:52.343
Now why would I ever consider
paying more than that?

153
00:17:52.378 --> 00:17:54.114
Because I intend
to squeeze you.

154
00:17:55.381 --> 00:17:58.151
I don't like
your kind of people.

155
00:17:58.186 --> 00:18:03.618
I don't like to see you
come out to this clean
country in oily hair

156
00:18:03.653 --> 00:18:06.192
dressed up in
those silk suits

157
00:18:06.227 --> 00:18:10.295
and try to pass yourselves off
as decent Americans.

158
00:18:10.330 --> 00:18:13.331
I'll do business with you.
but the fact is that

159
00:18:13.366 --> 00:18:15.795
I despise your masquerade.

160
00:18:15.830 --> 00:18:18.798
the dishonest way
you pose yourself.

161
00:18:18.833 --> 00:18:20.866
Yourself and your whole
fucking family.

162
00:18:28.843 --> 00:18:30.480
Senator.

163
00:18:31.846 --> 00:18:33.747
we're both part of
the same hypocrisy.

164
00:18:36.455 --> 00:18:38.917
But never think
it applies to my family.

165
00:18:40.591 --> 00:18:43.757
(DISMISSIVELY)
All right. all right.

166
00:18:43.792 --> 00:18:46.859
Some people have to
play little games.

167
00:18:46.894 --> 00:18:48.630
You play yours.

168
00:18:50.997 --> 00:18:55.868
So let's just say that
you'll pay me because it's
in your interest to pay me.

169
00:18:55.903 --> 00:18:58.904
But I want your answer
and the money
by noon tomorrow.

170
00:18:58.939 --> 00:19:00.411
And one more thing.

171
00:19:00.446 --> 00:19:03.975
Don't you
contact me again. ever.

172
00:19:04.010 --> 00:19:06.450
From now on
you deal with Turnbull.

173
00:19:06.485 --> 00:19:08.419
Open that door. son.

174
00:19:08.454 --> 00:19:12.390
Senator. you can have
my answer now if you like.

175
00:19:14.823 --> 00:19:16.394
My offer is this...

176
00:19:17.793 --> 00:19:19.496
Nothing.

177
00:19:21.027 --> 00:19:23.401
Not even the fee
for the gaming license.

178
00:19:23.436 --> 00:19:26.767
which I would appreciate if
you would put up personally.

179
00:19:29.970 --> 00:19:32.245
(CHUCKLING)

180
00:19:32.280 --> 00:19:33.609
Good afternoon.
gentlemen.

181
00:19:37.285 --> 00:19:39.879
Ladies! I didn't know
you were out here.

182
00:19:39.914 --> 00:19:41.584
Honey. we have
to go. We're 30 minutes late.

183
00:19:41.619 --> 00:19:43.718
KAY: Oh. really? I'm sorry.

184
00:19:43.753 --> 00:19:46.622
GEARY: Mrs. Corleone. it's
been delightful. Thank you.
KAY: Oh. no...

185
00:19:46.657 --> 00:19:49.460
It was our pleasure. Thank you
so much. it was wonderful
talking with you.

186
00:19:51.860 --> 00:19:54.234
(MUSIC PLAYING)
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

187
00:20:33.869 --> 00:20:39.004
Fredo! Fredo.
you son-of-a-bitch.
you look great!

188
00:20:39.039 --> 00:20:41.039
Frank Pentangeli!

189
00:20:41.074 --> 00:20:45.384
I thought you was
never coming out west.
you big bum!

190
00:20:45.419 --> 00:20:47.881
I've got to check
on my boys.

191
00:20:47.916 --> 00:20:51.357
Hey. Fredo. what's with
the food here?
What's the matter?

192
00:20:51.392 --> 00:20:53.425
A kid comes up to me
in a white jacket.

193
00:20:53.460 --> 00:20:57.363
gives me a Ritz cracker
with chopped liver
and says. "canapes".

194
00:20:57.398 --> 00:21:02.467
I said. "Can of peas. my ass.
That's a Ritz cracker
and chopped liver!"

195
00:21:02.502 --> 00:21:05.767
(LAUGHING)

196
00:21:05.802 --> 00:21:09.441
Bring out the peppers
and sardines!

197
00:21:09.476 --> 00:21:12.774
Oh. seeing you
reminds me of New York.
the old days!

198
00:21:12.809 --> 00:21:14.974
Hey. Fredo.

199
00:21:15.009 --> 00:21:18.681
you remember. uh. Willi Cicci.
who was with old man
Clemenza in Brooklyn?

200
00:21:19.915 --> 00:21:21.849
Yeah. look here...

201
00:21:21.884 --> 00:21:25.457
We were all
upset about that. Frankie.
Heart attack. huh?

202
00:21:25.492 --> 00:21:27.558
No. no. that was
no heart attack.

203
00:21:27.593 --> 00:21:32.860
That's... That's what I'm here
to see your brother
Mike about.

204
00:21:32.895 --> 00:21:34.763
But what's
with him?

205
00:21:34.798 --> 00:21:35.995
What do you mean?

206
00:21:36.030 --> 00:21:38.371
I mean.
what do I got to do.

207
00:21:38.406 --> 00:21:41.605
do I have to get
a letter of introduction
to get a sit-down?

208
00:21:41.640 --> 00:21:43.673
You...you can't get in
to see Mike?

209
00:21:43.708 --> 00:21:45.939
He's got me
waiting in a lobby!

210
00:21:49.681 --> 00:21:50.977
Johnny Ola.

211
00:21:51.012 --> 00:21:52.913
Al Neri.

212
00:21:58.151 --> 00:22:01.152
Do you know my lawyer
Tom Hagen? Johnny Ola...
Sure...

213
00:22:01.187 --> 00:22:03.792
I remember Tom
from the old days.

214
00:22:03.827 --> 00:22:05.563
Rocco.

215
00:22:05.598 --> 00:22:06.861
What's this?

216
00:22:06.896 --> 00:22:09.402
It's an orange
from Miami.

217
00:22:09.437 --> 00:22:11.030
Why don't you take care
of Johnny's men?

218
00:22:11.065 --> 00:22:12.669
They look like
they might be hungry.

219
00:22:12.704 --> 00:22:13.901
Johnny?

220
00:22:16.543 --> 00:22:18.169
Tom isn't gonna sit in
with us. Johnny.

221
00:22:18.204 --> 00:22:21.843
He only handles specific areas
of the family business. Tom...

222
00:22:21.878 --> 00:22:23.977
Sure. Mike.

223
00:22:27.983 --> 00:22:29.950
What are you
drinking. Johnny?

224
00:22:29.985 --> 00:22:32.084
Anisette.

225
00:22:32.119 --> 00:22:33.756
Anisette.

226
00:22:36.497 --> 00:22:38.926
If you need anything. Mike.
I'll be outside. all right?

227
00:22:38.961 --> 00:22:40.895
MICHAEL: Just tell Rocco
we're waiting. Tom.

228
00:22:46.936 --> 00:22:49.607
JOHNNY: I just left. uh.
Mr. Roth in Miami.

229
00:22:49.642 --> 00:22:51.202
MICHAEL: How is his health?

230
00:22:51.237 --> 00:22:54.480
JOHNNY: Ahh. it's not good.
(SIGHS)

231
00:22:54.515 --> 00:22:56.911
MICHAEL: Is there anything
I can do. anything I can send?

232
00:22:56.946 --> 00:23:00.145
JOHNNY: He appreciates
your concern. Michael.
and your respect.

233
00:23:01.918 --> 00:23:03.885
That casino you are
interested in...

234
00:23:03.920 --> 00:23:06.690
The registered owners are
Jacob Lawrence.
Allan Barclay.

235
00:23:06.725 --> 00:23:09.528
Both Beverly Hills
attorneys.

236
00:23:09.563 --> 00:23:12.630
The real owners are the old
Lakeville Road group
from Cleveland

237
00:23:12.665 --> 00:23:14.962
and our friend
in Miami.

238
00:23:14.997 --> 00:23:17.129
Meyer Klingman runs it

239
00:23:17.164 --> 00:23:19.571
he owns a piece
of it too. he does all right.

240
00:23:19.606 --> 00:23:21.672
But I've been
instructed to tell you

241
00:23:21.707 --> 00:23:24.642
that if you move Klingman out.
our friend in Miami
will go along.

242
00:23:27.614 --> 00:23:29.779
It's very kind of him.

243
00:23:29.814 --> 00:23:33.486
You tell him
it's greatly appreciated.

244
00:23:33.521 --> 00:23:36.456
Hyman Roth
always makes money
for his partners.

245
00:23:38.823 --> 00:23:42.825
One by one.
our old friends are gone.

246
00:23:42.860 --> 00:23:46.125
Death. natural or not.

247
00:23:46.160 --> 00:23:48.996
prison. deported...

248
00:23:50.538 --> 00:23:52.835
Hyman Roth
is the only one left.

249
00:23:52.870 --> 00:23:56.135
because he always
made money
for his partners.

250
00:23:56.170 --> 00:23:57.873
(GRUNTS)

251
00:23:57.908 --> 00:24:00.909
I can't believe it! Out of
30 professional musicians

252
00:24:00.944 --> 00:24:03.175
there isn't one Italian in.
in the group here.

253
00:24:03.210 --> 00:24:06.046
Come on. Let's have
a tarantella! Come on...

254
00:24:06.081 --> 00:24:07.916
(VOCALIZING)

255
00:24:07.951 --> 00:24:11.524
(PIANO PLAYING)

256
00:24:11.559 --> 00:24:14.285
You! Up!
Clarinet up. up. up!

257
00:24:14.320 --> 00:24:16.826
(HUMMING TARANTELLA)

258
00:24:23.296 --> 00:24:24.669
<i>Questa mano!</i>

259
00:24:24.704 --> 00:24:26.000
(HUMMING)

260
00:24:26.035 --> 00:24:28.035
<i>Questa mano!</i>

261
00:24:29.940 --> 00:24:32.941
(PLAYING<i> POP!</i>
<i>GOES THE WEASEL)</i>

262
00:24:32.976 --> 00:24:35.713
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)
What the hell
have we here?

263
00:24:36.881 --> 00:24:38.078
(BAND PLAYING MUSIC)

264
00:24:38.113 --> 00:24:40.245
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

265
00:24:40.280 --> 00:24:42.049
(GUESTS APPLAUDING)

266
00:24:47.694 --> 00:24:50.057
I'll see my
sister alone.

267
00:24:50.092 --> 00:24:53.225
It concerns me too.
Is it okay if I stay?

268
00:24:53.260 --> 00:24:57.801
How are you. honey?
You've met Merle.
he was with me in Vegas.

269
00:24:57.836 --> 00:24:59.803
I saw him with you.

270
00:24:59.838 --> 00:25:01.266
Could I have a drink
or something?

271
00:25:05.338 --> 00:25:07.239
Al. please
get him a drink!

272
00:25:09.914 --> 00:25:14.048
We're going to Europe.
I'd like to book
passage on<i> The Queen.</i>

273
00:25:14.083 --> 00:25:16.919
So what do you come to me for?
Why don't you go
to a travel agent?

274
00:25:16.954 --> 00:25:18.217
We're getting
married first.

275
00:25:27.701 --> 00:25:30.702
The ink on your divorce
isn't dry yet.
and you're getting married?

276
00:25:34.037 --> 00:25:36.840
You see your children
on weekends.

277
00:25:36.875 --> 00:25:39.337
You know your oldest boy.
Victor. was picked up in Reno

278
00:25:39.372 --> 00:25:41.911
for some petty theft
you don't even know about.
Michael!

279
00:25:41.946 --> 00:25:45.244
You fly around the world
with men who don't care for
you and use you like a whore.

280
00:25:45.279 --> 00:25:46.718
You're not my father!

281
00:25:46.753 --> 00:25:47.950
Then what do you
come to me for?

282
00:25:47.985 --> 00:25:49.347
'Cause I need money.

283
00:26:02.868 --> 00:26:05.671
Connie. Connie. Connie.
Connie. Connie. Connie...

284
00:26:08.335 --> 00:26:09.972
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

285
00:26:12.042 --> 00:26:13.712
I want to be
reasonable with you.

286
00:26:15.848 --> 00:26:19.751
Now why don't you stay
with us...with the family?

287
00:26:19.786 --> 00:26:22.314
You can live on the estate
with your kids.

288
00:26:22.349 --> 00:26:23.854
You won't be deprived
of anything.

289
00:26:23.889 --> 00:26:25.185
You can have everything
you want.

290
00:26:30.291 --> 00:26:33.897
I don't know this Merle.
I don't know what he does

291
00:26:33.932 --> 00:26:37.263
I don't know what he lives on.

292
00:26:37.298 --> 00:26:39.672
Now why don't you
tell him that marriage
is out of the question.

293
00:26:39.707 --> 00:26:41.366
and you don't want
to see him anymore.

294
00:26:42.842 --> 00:26:44.974
He'll understand.
believe me.

295
00:26:45.009 --> 00:26:46.371
(EXHALES FORCEFULLY)

296
00:26:53.083 --> 00:26:54.379
Connie.

297
00:26:56.955 --> 00:26:58.251
If you don't
listen to me

298
00:26:59.353 --> 00:27:00.858
and marry this man.

299
00:27:05.766 --> 00:27:07.260
you'll disappoint me.

300
00:27:15.369 --> 00:27:18.909
(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING
OVER P.A.)

301
00:27:39.393 --> 00:27:41.228
WOMAN:<i> Famiglia!</i>

302
00:27:41.263 --> 00:27:44.099
ALL:<i> Cent' anni!</i>

303
00:27:44.134 --> 00:27:46.365
What's
"Chen dannay"?

304
00:27:46.400 --> 00:27:49.368
<i>"Cent' anni".</i>
<i>It means 100 years.</i>

305
00:27:49.403 --> 00:27:53.911
It means we should
all live happily for
100 years. The family.

306
00:27:53.946 --> 00:27:56.078
It would be true
if my father were alive.

307
00:27:56.113 --> 00:27:57.849
MAMA CORLEONE: Connie.

308
00:27:57.884 --> 00:27:59.510
Hey...

309
00:27:59.545 --> 00:28:02.348
Merle. you've met my
sister-in-law. Deanna.

310
00:28:03.549 --> 00:28:05.021
Fredo's wife.
My pleasure.

311
00:28:05.056 --> 00:28:06.319
How do you do?

312
00:28:06.354 --> 00:28:09.487
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

313
00:28:11.458 --> 00:28:15.394
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

314
00:28:22.843 --> 00:28:24.073
(EXCLAIMS IN ITALIAN)

315
00:28:28.112 --> 00:28:30.112
(BAND PLAYING MUSIC)

316
00:28:45.965 --> 00:28:47.426
(INAUDIBLE)

317
00:28:52.400 --> 00:28:55.335
(DRUNKENLY) What's the matter?
I just...I just want to dance!

318
00:28:55.370 --> 00:28:57.810
Dancing is one thing...
you're falling
all over the floor.

319
00:28:57.845 --> 00:28:59.306
DEANNA: Oh. I know
what's the matter with you.

320
00:28:59.341 --> 00:29:01.539
You're just jealous
because he's a real man!

321
00:29:01.574 --> 00:29:04.410
I swear to God. Deanna.
I'm going to belt you
right in the teeth.

322
00:29:04.445 --> 00:29:06.885
Ah! You couldn't belt
your mama!

323
00:29:06.920 --> 00:29:08.414
You know something...

324
00:29:08.449 --> 00:29:10.317
These Dagos are crazy
when it comes to their wives.

325
00:29:10.352 --> 00:29:13.221
Michael says
that if you can't
take care of this.

326
00:29:13.256 --> 00:29:15.520
I have to.

327
00:29:15.555 --> 00:29:17.060
I think
you'd better.

328
00:29:17.095 --> 00:29:18.523
DEANNA:
Never marry a Wop.

329
00:29:18.558 --> 00:29:20.899
They treat their
wives like shit!

330
00:29:20.934 --> 00:29:22.197
I didn't mean
to say Wop.

331
00:29:22.232 --> 00:29:25.101
(SCREAMS) Don't! Rocco!

332
00:29:25.136 --> 00:29:30.205
What are you doing to me.
you big slob? Help!

333
00:29:30.240 --> 00:29:31.503
Fredo!

334
00:29:31.538 --> 00:29:33.142
I can't control
her. Mikey.

335
00:29:33.177 --> 00:29:35.441
You're my brother.
you don't have to apologize.

336
00:29:40.283 --> 00:29:44.384
Clemenza promised the Rosato
brothers three territories in
the Bronx after he died.

337
00:29:44.419 --> 00:29:46.023
You took over and
you didn't give it to them.

338
00:29:46.058 --> 00:29:47.387
I welched.
MICHAEL: You welched.

339
00:29:47.422 --> 00:29:50.522
Yeah. Clemenza promised them
<i>lu cazzo.</i>

340
00:29:50.557 --> 00:29:52.392
Clemenza promised them
nothing.

341
00:29:52.427 --> 00:29:54.933
He hated those
son-of-a-bitches
more than I do.

342
00:29:54.968 --> 00:29:57.430
Frankie.
they feel cheated.

343
00:29:57.465 --> 00:30:02.468
Michael...you're sitting high
up in the Sierra mountains.
And you're drinking. uh...

344
00:30:02.503 --> 00:30:04.206
What's he drinking?

345
00:30:04.241 --> 00:30:07.176
Champagne.
Champagne.
Champagne cocktails.

346
00:30:07.211 --> 00:30:09.948
And passing judgment
on how I run my family.

347
00:30:11.083 --> 00:30:12.379
(IN ITALIAN)

348
00:30:19.289 --> 00:30:21.223
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

349
00:30:33.435 --> 00:30:35.600
You're a good old man

350
00:30:35.635 --> 00:30:38.141
and I like you.

351
00:30:38.176 --> 00:30:40.506
You were loyal
to my father for years.

352
00:30:42.180 --> 00:30:45.544
The Rosato brothers
are taking hostages.

353
00:30:47.416 --> 00:30:50.648
They spit
right in my face.

354
00:30:50.683 --> 00:30:53.321
all because
they're backed up
by that Jew in Miami.

355
00:30:53.356 --> 00:30:56.225
I know.
That's why I don't
want them touched.

356
00:30:56.260 --> 00:30:58.029
You don't want
'em touched?
No.

357
00:30:58.064 --> 00:31:00.262
I want you
to be fair with them.

358
00:31:00.297 --> 00:31:02.935
You want me to
be fair with them?

359
00:31:02.970 --> 00:31:05.399
(LAUGHS) How can you
be fair to animals?

360
00:31:05.434 --> 00:31:11.603
Tom. for Crissakes. listen.
They recruit spics.
they recruit niggers.

361
00:31:11.638 --> 00:31:15.475
They do violence in their...
in their Grandmothers'
neighborhoods!

362
00:31:15.510 --> 00:31:19.083
And I tell you. everything
with them is whores! Whores!

363
00:31:19.118 --> 00:31:22.185
And junk. dope!

364
00:31:22.220 --> 00:31:24.715
And they leave
the gambling to last.

365
00:31:24.750 --> 00:31:28.026
I want to run my family
without you on my back.

366
00:31:28.061 --> 00:31:30.193
And I want those
Rosatos dead!

367
00:31:30.228 --> 00:31:31.557
No.

368
00:31:31.592 --> 00:31:33.097
<i>Morti.</i>

369
00:31:38.599 --> 00:31:41.732
Now I have business
that's important
with Hyman Roth.

370
00:31:41.767 --> 00:31:43.371
I don't want it
disturbed.

371
00:31:45.441 --> 00:31:47.672
And you give
your loyalty to a Jew
before your own blood.

372
00:31:51.084 --> 00:31:53.150
Come on. Frankie.

373
00:31:53.185 --> 00:31:56.681
you know my father did
business with Hyman Roth.
He respected him.

374
00:31:56.716 --> 00:32:01.620
Your father did business
with Hyman Roth. your father
respected Hyman Roth.

375
00:32:01.655 --> 00:32:04.623
but your father
never trusted Hyman Roth

376
00:32:04.658 --> 00:32:07.659
or his Sicilian
messenger boy.
Johnny Ola.

377
00:32:07.694 --> 00:32:09.595
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

378
00:32:16.142 --> 00:32:18.571
(IN ENGLISH) I want
everybody here to know.

379
00:32:18.606 --> 00:32:21.673
there's not going to be
no trouble from me!

380
00:32:21.708 --> 00:32:23.708
Don Corleone.

381
00:32:23.743 --> 00:32:25.710
(IN ITALIAN)

382
00:32:30.750 --> 00:32:32.420
(DOOR SLAMMING)

383
00:32:32.455 --> 00:32:34.158
(SIGHS)

384
00:32:34.193 --> 00:32:35.720
You want him
to leave now?

385
00:32:38.725 --> 00:32:40.494
Let him go back
to New York.

386
00:32:40.529 --> 00:32:42.430
I've already made
my plans.

387
00:32:44.203 --> 00:32:45.730
The old man
had too much wine.

388
00:32:51.243 --> 00:32:52.539
It's late.

389
00:32:53.806 --> 00:32:55.641
(BAND PLAYING MUSIC)

390
00:33:05.158 --> 00:33:07.158
How's the baby?

391
00:33:07.193 --> 00:33:08.753
Sleeping inside me.

392
00:33:10.295 --> 00:33:11.756
Does it feel
like a boy?

393
00:33:11.791 --> 00:33:14.099
Yes. Yes. it does. Michael.

394
00:33:17.236 --> 00:33:19.071
Kay?
Hmm?

395
00:33:19.106 --> 00:33:21.667
I'm sorry about
all the people today.

396
00:33:21.702 --> 00:33:23.603
Bad timing.

397
00:33:23.638 --> 00:33:26.111
It couldn't be
helped. though.

398
00:33:26.146 --> 00:33:28.377
It made me think
of what you once
told me.

399
00:33:31.250 --> 00:33:32.810
"In five years
the Corleone family

400
00:33:32.845 --> 00:33:35.483
"will be completely
legitimate."

401
00:33:35.518 --> 00:33:37.452
That was
seven years ago.

402
00:33:40.787 --> 00:33:44.294
I know.
I'm trying. darling.

403
00:34:48.624 --> 00:34:49.920
Did you see this?

404
00:34:49.955 --> 00:34:51.559
Mmm-hmm.

405
00:35:00.471 --> 00:35:02.471
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

406
00:35:04.937 --> 00:35:06.706
Michael. why are
the drapes open?

407
00:35:12.747 --> 00:35:14.219
(GUN FIRING)

408
00:35:22.889 --> 00:35:24.361
(GUNFIRE STOPS)

409
00:35:24.396 --> 00:35:26.528
(SHATTERED GLASS TINKLING)

410
00:35:27.894 --> 00:35:30.466
(MICHAEL PANTING)

411
00:35:34.769 --> 00:35:36.736
Kay. are you
all right?

412
00:35:36.771 --> 00:35:38.540
Are you hit?

413
00:35:38.575 --> 00:35:40.344
(PANTING) No.

414
00:35:41.743 --> 00:35:43.611
(SOOTHINGLY)
It's over. It's over.

415
00:35:43.646 --> 00:35:45.547
(ALARM RINGING)

416
00:35:45.582 --> 00:35:47.714
MAN: Stop! Stop!

417
00:35:49.553 --> 00:35:50.651
Halt!

418
00:35:50.686 --> 00:35:52.191
(TIRES SCREECHING)

419
00:35:57.792 --> 00:36:00.199
(DOGS BARKING)

420
00:36:01.862 --> 00:36:03.466
They're still
on the property.

421
00:36:03.501 --> 00:36:05.699
Please Michael.
Please stay inside.

422
00:36:05.734 --> 00:36:07.503
Keep them alive.
We'll try.

423
00:36:07.538 --> 00:36:08.867
Rocco! Alive!

424
00:36:10.574 --> 00:36:11.837
Stay by the door.

425
00:36:15.843 --> 00:36:18.943
(ALL CLAMORING)

426
00:36:20.353 --> 00:36:22.254
(DOGS BARKING)

427
00:36:26.821 --> 00:36:28.590
(TIRES SCREECHING)

428
00:36:51.010 --> 00:36:53.483
(EXHALES SLOWLY)

429
00:37:21.975 --> 00:37:26.318
(MAN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

430
00:37:30.918 --> 00:37:32.390
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

431
00:37:32.425 --> 00:37:33.589
Yeah. come in.

432
00:37:41.533 --> 00:37:42.862
Mikey. are you
all right?

433
00:37:42.897 --> 00:37:44.435
Yeah.
Yeah.

434
00:37:48.639 --> 00:37:50.639
There's a lot
I can't tell you. Tom.

435
00:37:53.006 --> 00:37:55.413
And I know
that's upset you
in the past.

436
00:37:55.448 --> 00:37:57.580
A little.
Yeah.

437
00:37:57.615 --> 00:38:00.682
You felt it was because
of some lack of trust
or confidence.

438
00:38:02.917 --> 00:38:07.821
But it's...it's because
I admire you and love you

439
00:38:07.856 --> 00:38:09.559
that I kept things
secret from you.

440
00:38:12.498 --> 00:38:15.433
That's why at his moment
you're the only one
I completely trust.

441
00:38:18.504 --> 00:38:20.064
Fredo?

442
00:38:20.099 --> 00:38:21.538
Well. he's got
a good heart.

443
00:38:22.805 --> 00:38:25.102
But he's weak
and he's stupid.

444
00:38:25.137 --> 00:38:26.972
and this is
life and death.

445
00:38:28.514 --> 00:38:31.449
Tom. you're my brother.

446
00:38:34.817 --> 00:38:37.081
(SIGHS)

447
00:38:37.116 --> 00:38:40.920
(VOICE TREMBLING) I always
wanted to be thought of
as a brother by you. Mikey.

448
00:38:40.955 --> 00:38:42.592
A real brother.

449
00:38:45.091 --> 00:38:46.497
I know that.

450
00:38:52.967 --> 00:38:54.703
You're going
to take over.

451
00:38:56.168 --> 00:38:57.937
You're going to be
the Don.

452
00:39:01.613 --> 00:39:03.778
If what I think
has happened.
has happened.

453
00:39:04.880 --> 00:39:06.715
I'm leaving here tonight.

454
00:39:07.916 --> 00:39:09.586
I give you
complete power.

455
00:39:09.621 --> 00:39:12.853
Over Fredo and his men.
Rocco. Neri. everyone.

456
00:39:15.759 --> 00:39:20.861
I'm trusting you
with the lives of my wife
and my children.

457
00:39:20.896 --> 00:39:22.566
the future of this family.

458
00:39:25.769 --> 00:39:28.935
If we catch these guys
do you think we'll be able to
find out who's backing them?

459
00:39:28.970 --> 00:39:30.805
MICHAEL: We're not gonna
catch them.

460
00:39:32.809 --> 00:39:34.875
Unless I'm very wrong.
they're dead already.

461
00:39:37.649 --> 00:39:39.583
They were killed
by somebody close to us.

462
00:39:40.850 --> 00:39:42.586
Inside.

463
00:39:42.621 --> 00:39:44.786
Very. very frightened
that they botched it.

464
00:39:46.152 --> 00:39:48.020
What about your people Rocco
and Neri?

465
00:39:48.055 --> 00:39:50.594
You don't think that they had
something to do with this.

466
00:39:53.797 --> 00:39:55.126
You see...

467
00:39:55.161 --> 00:39:57.799
All our people
are businessmen.

468
00:39:59.737 --> 00:40:01.506
Their loyalty
is based on that.

469
00:40:05.138 --> 00:40:07.171
One thing I learned
from Pop

470
00:40:09.109 --> 00:40:11.813
was to try to think
as people around you think.

471
00:40:14.752 --> 00:40:17.753
And on that basis.
anything is possible.

472
00:40:17.788 --> 00:40:19.249
(SCREAMING)

473
00:40:19.284 --> 00:40:23.220
Mike. they're dead!
Right outside my window!

474
00:40:23.255 --> 00:40:26.795
I want to get out of here.
They're lying there dead!

475
00:40:26.830 --> 00:40:28.863
(SCREAMING)

476
00:40:30.966 --> 00:40:32.702
(DOGS BARKING)

477
00:40:37.808 --> 00:40:40.743
MAN: Over here!
There's two of them.

478
00:40:40.778 --> 00:40:43.845
Looks like they were
hired out of New York.
I don't recognize them.

479
00:40:45.211 --> 00:40:47.112
You won't get anything
out of them now.

480
00:40:48.280 --> 00:40:49.950
Fish them out.

481
00:41:15.043 --> 00:41:17.208
All right.
Get rid of the bodies.

482
00:41:17.243 --> 00:41:18.781
Where's Mike?

483
00:41:18.816 --> 00:41:20.178
Rocco.

484
00:41:50.650 --> 00:41:52.243
(WHISPERING)
Anthony.

485
00:41:52.278 --> 00:41:55.147
everything is going
to be all right.
Try to sleep.

486
00:42:12.001 --> 00:42:13.704
Did you like
your party?

487
00:42:15.037 --> 00:42:16.641
I got lots
of presents.

488
00:42:16.676 --> 00:42:18.907
MICHAEL: I know.

489
00:42:18.942 --> 00:42:20.744
Did you like them?

490
00:42:20.779 --> 00:42:23.945
Yeah. I didn't know
the people who gave them
to me.

491
00:42:23.980 --> 00:42:25.848
Hmm. Well. they were friends.

492
00:42:28.754 --> 00:42:30.754
Did you see
my present for you?

493
00:42:30.789 --> 00:42:32.217
MICHAEL: It was on my pillow.

494
00:42:35.761 --> 00:42:39.697
Anthony. I'm going to be
leaving very early tomorrow.

495
00:42:39.732 --> 00:42:41.864
Will you take me?

496
00:42:41.899 --> 00:42:43.965
MICHAEL: No. I can't. Anthony.

497
00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:45.670
Why do you have to go?

498
00:42:47.003 --> 00:42:49.707
Because I have to do
business.

499
00:42:49.742 --> 00:42:51.610
I could help you.

500
00:42:54.879 --> 00:42:56.307
I know.

501
00:42:56.342 --> 00:42:58.210
Some day you will.

502
00:42:59.686 --> 00:43:01.180
Get some sleep.

503
00:43:47.833 --> 00:43:49.998
(COOING)

504
00:43:59.075 --> 00:44:04.078
(ALL SINGING IN ITALIAN)

505
00:44:18.765 --> 00:44:21.161
(IN ITALIAN)

506
00:44:31.943 --> 00:44:33.778
(MAN WOLF-WHISTLING)

507
00:44:40.952 --> 00:44:43.084
(CROWD CHEERING
AND APPLAUDING)

508
00:44:46.023 --> 00:44:47.792
(BAND PLAYING MUSIC)

509
00:44:55.802 --> 00:44:58.737
(IN ITALIAN)

510
00:45:18.484 --> 00:45:20.088
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

511
00:45:20.123 --> 00:45:22.453
(CHUCKLES)

512
00:45:22.488 --> 00:45:25.027
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

513
00:45:38.537 --> 00:45:40.240
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

514
00:45:49.922 --> 00:45:51.548
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

515
00:45:51.583 --> 00:45:55.288
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

516
00:45:55.323 --> 00:45:57.422
<i>Mamma! Mamma mia!</i>

517
00:45:57.457 --> 00:46:00.095
(SOBBING)
(BAND PLAYS MUSIC)

518
00:46:07.302 --> 00:46:10.072
(SINGING IN ITALIAN)

519
00:46:45.307 --> 00:46:47.307
(SPEAKING SOFTLY
IN ITALIAN)

520
00:47:31.056 --> 00:47:32.352
(GASPS)

521
00:47:36.655 --> 00:47:39.491
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

522
00:47:39.526 --> 00:47:41.262
(IN ENGLISH) Let's go see her
backstage.

523
00:47:43.299 --> 00:47:45.200
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

524
00:47:52.704 --> 00:47:55.045
(MAN SPEAKING ITALIAN)

525
00:48:08.995 --> 00:48:10.390
(GASPING)

526
00:48:10.425 --> 00:48:11.622
(PROTESTING)

527
00:48:11.657 --> 00:48:14.966
(FANUCCI SPEAKING ITALIAN)

528
00:48:19.302 --> 00:48:21.038
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

529
00:48:21.073 --> 00:48:23.040
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

530
00:48:30.445 --> 00:48:32.148
(FANUCCI SPEAKING ITALIAN)

531
00:48:36.418 --> 00:48:37.989
(IN ENGLISH)
Vito. come on.

532
00:48:45.295 --> 00:48:47.394
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

533
00:49:07.680 --> 00:49:09.383
(CONTINUE CHATTERING
IN ITALIAN)

534
00:49:55.827 --> 00:49:57.332
(IN ITALIAN)

535
00:50:09.709 --> 00:50:11.478
(MAN BECKONING)

536
00:50:13.515 --> 00:50:14.712
(BECKONING)

537
00:50:20.357 --> 00:50:22.423
MAN: Hey.
you speak Italian?

538
00:50:29.333 --> 00:50:30.629
(CLEMENZA SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

539
00:51:12.838 --> 00:51:14.673
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

540
00:51:22.881 --> 00:51:24.320
(MUTTERS)

541
00:51:24.355 --> 00:51:25.684
(CASH REGISTER BELL DINGS)

542
00:51:25.719 --> 00:51:27.356
(LAUGHING)

543
00:51:31.461 --> 00:51:32.823
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

544
00:51:49.215 --> 00:51:51.479
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

545
00:52:08.630 --> 00:52:10.630
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

546
00:52:23.645 --> 00:52:26.250
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

547
00:52:58.680 --> 00:53:00.251
(MUTTERING)

548
00:53:29.315 --> 00:53:30.710
MAN: Vito!

549
00:53:35.585 --> 00:53:38.916
Oh. no. no! No.

550
00:53:38.951 --> 00:53:40.555
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

551
00:53:45.430 --> 00:53:49.597
(CONTINUE CHATTERING
IN ITALIAN)

552
00:54:19.893 --> 00:54:22.025
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

553
00:54:45.721 --> 00:54:48.326
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

554
00:55:38.004 --> 00:55:39.773
(IN ENGLISH)
Yeah. sure.

555
00:55:39.808 --> 00:55:41.544
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

556
00:56:32.861 --> 00:56:35.059
(IN ENGLISH)
Come on in.

557
00:56:35.094 --> 00:56:37.127
Hey. Vito. come on in!

558
00:56:37.162 --> 00:56:39.030
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

559
00:57:00.724 --> 00:57:02.251
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

560
00:57:02.286 --> 00:57:04.154
(REPLIES AFFIRMATIVELY
IN ITALIAN)

561
00:57:43.569 --> 00:57:44.832
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

562
00:57:51.577 --> 00:57:54.677
(DOORBELL CHIMING)

563
00:58:00.586 --> 00:58:03.983
(DOORBELL CHIMING)

564
00:58:16.833 --> 00:58:18.162
(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

565
00:58:54.805 --> 00:58:57.938
(SINGING SOFTLY
IN ITALIAN)

566
00:59:02.714 --> 00:59:04.076
(BABY CRYING)

567
00:59:06.916 --> 00:59:09.246
(CONTINUES CRYING)

568
00:59:17.795 --> 00:59:19.322
(SOBBING)

569
00:59:27.431 --> 00:59:30.707
(TRAIN HORN BLOWING)

570
01:01:46.009 --> 01:01:47.371
MRS. ROTH: Come on in.

571
01:01:49.914 --> 01:01:52.475
It's all right. Come on.
Hyman's in there.

572
01:01:52.510 --> 01:01:53.850
I was just making
some lunch...

573
01:01:53.885 --> 01:01:55.852
Would you like
a tuna sandwich?

574
01:01:55.887 --> 01:01:57.854
Uh. no. thank you.

575
01:01:57.889 --> 01:02:01.825
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
ON TV)

576
01:02:04.192 --> 01:02:08.865
MAN: (ON TV)
<i>...pick up of two by Holden.</i>
<i>Second and eight for S.C...</i>

577
01:02:08.900 --> 01:02:10.900
MICHAEL: Mr. Roth?

578
01:02:10.935 --> 01:02:12.803
Come in. Michael.
(CLEARS THROAT)

579
01:02:14.466 --> 01:02:16.499
Sit down.
make yourself
comfortable.

580
01:02:18.602 --> 01:02:20.239
It's almost over.

581
01:02:22.881 --> 01:02:24.276
Do you follow
the football game?

582
01:02:26.181 --> 01:02:28.181
Not for a while
I haven't.

583
01:02:28.216 --> 01:02:31.184
I enjoy watching football
in the afternoon.

584
01:02:31.219 --> 01:02:34.220
One of the things I love
about this country.

585
01:02:34.255 --> 01:02:36.354
Baseball too.

586
01:02:36.389 --> 01:02:38.389
I love baseball...

587
01:02:38.424 --> 01:02:42.360
ever since Arnold Rothstein
fixed the World Series
in 1919.

588
01:02:42.395 --> 01:02:43.999
(ROTH CHUCKLING)

589
01:02:48.368 --> 01:02:49.466
I heard you had some trouble.

590
01:02:53.472 --> 01:02:54.812
Stupid.

591
01:02:56.376 --> 01:02:58.409
People behaving like that
with guns.

592
01:03:01.249 --> 01:03:03.051
The important thing is
you're all right.

593
01:03:04.318 --> 01:03:08.254
Good health is the most
important thing.

594
01:03:08.289 --> 01:03:10.388
More than success.
more than money.

595
01:03:12.898 --> 01:03:15.162
More than power.

596
01:03:15.197 --> 01:03:16.526
(OBJECTS CLATTERING)

597
01:03:21.566 --> 01:03:23.907
(RAISES TV VOLUME)

598
01:03:25.240 --> 01:03:26.602
(CLEARS THROAT)

599
01:03:28.980 --> 01:03:31.211
(SOFTLY) I came here
because there's going to be
more bloodshed.

600
01:03:33.050 --> 01:03:34.544
I want you to know about it
before it happens

601
01:03:34.579 --> 01:03:36.854
so that there's no danger
of starting another war.

602
01:03:37.681 --> 01:03:39.252
Nobody wants
another war.

603
01:03:41.322 --> 01:03:45.093
Frank Pentangeli came
to my home and he asked
my permission

604
01:03:45.128 --> 01:03:46.963
to get rid of
the Rosato brothers.

605
01:03:46.998 --> 01:03:49.262
When I refused he tried to
have me killed.

606
01:03:49.297 --> 01:03:51.000
He was stupid.
I was lucky.

607
01:03:51.035 --> 01:03:52.903
I'll visit him soon.

608
01:03:52.938 --> 01:03:55.598
The important thing
is that nothing

609
01:03:55.633 --> 01:03:58.634
interferes with our
plans for the future.
Yours and mine.

610
01:03:58.669 --> 01:04:00.471
Nothing is
more important.

611
01:04:03.311 --> 01:04:05.179
You're a wise and
a considerate young man.

612
01:04:06.446 --> 01:04:07.984
And you're a great
man. Mr. Roth.

613
01:04:09.317 --> 01:04:10.646
There's much
I can learn from you.

614
01:04:12.188 --> 01:04:13.924
Whatever I can do
to help. Michael.

615
01:04:16.357 --> 01:04:17.928
MRS. ROTH: Excuse me.
Lunch.

616
01:04:17.963 --> 01:04:19.358
Come in.

617
01:04:19.393 --> 01:04:21.030
Thank you.
my dear.

618
01:04:21.065 --> 01:04:23.692
Honey Bunny. you're going to
break your eardrums.

619
01:04:23.727 --> 01:04:26.101
(LOWERS TV VOLUME)
Enjoy it.

620
01:04:26.136 --> 01:04:27.465
ROTH: Thank you.

621
01:04:30.371 --> 01:04:31.568
(DOOR CLOSES)

622
01:04:33.308 --> 01:04:35.242
You're young.
I'm old and sick.

623
01:04:37.213 --> 01:04:40.181
What we'll do
in the next few months

624
01:04:40.216 --> 01:04:42.381
will make history. Michael.

625
01:04:42.416 --> 01:04:45.252
History. It's never been
done before.

626
01:04:45.287 --> 01:04:47.518
Not even your father
would dream

627
01:04:47.553 --> 01:04:49.289
that such a thing
could be possible.

628
01:04:52.129 --> 01:04:54.690
Then Pentangeli
is a dead man.

629
01:04:54.725 --> 01:04:56.263
You don't object?

630
01:04:57.761 --> 01:04:59.530
He's small potatoes.

631
01:05:07.507 --> 01:05:09.177
MAN: Hey Cicc'!

632
01:05:10.675 --> 01:05:12.147
What's up?

633
01:05:15.449 --> 01:05:17.185
We got company. huh?

634
01:05:31.564 --> 01:05:33.267
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

635
01:05:56.655 --> 01:05:58.523
Don Corleone.

636
01:05:58.558 --> 01:06:00.426
I... I wish you would
have let me know
you were coming.

637
01:06:00.461 --> 01:06:02.791
I could have
prepared something for you.

638
01:06:02.826 --> 01:06:04.595
I didn't want you
to know I was coming.

639
01:06:09.074 --> 01:06:10.370
(DOORS CLOSING)

640
01:06:12.374 --> 01:06:14.110
You heard what happened
in my home?

641
01:06:14.145 --> 01:06:16.475
Mike. I almost died myself.
we was all so relieved...

642
01:06:16.510 --> 01:06:18.114
In my home!

643
01:06:21.449 --> 01:06:24.120
In my bedroom
where my wife sleeps!

644
01:06:27.257 --> 01:06:29.488
Where my children
come to play with their toys.

645
01:06:31.228 --> 01:06:33.030
In my home.

646
01:06:50.280 --> 01:06:52.148
I want you to help me
take my revenge.

647
01:06:53.415 --> 01:06:56.350
Michael. anything.
What can I do?

648
01:07:00.191 --> 01:07:02.191
Settle these troubles
with the Rosato brothers.

649
01:07:03.524 --> 01:07:06.195
Mike. I don't understand.
I don't...

650
01:07:06.230 --> 01:07:09.561
Look. I don't have
your brain for big deals.

651
01:07:09.596 --> 01:07:11.167
But this is
a street thing.

652
01:07:11.202 --> 01:07:14.203
That Hyman Roth
in Miami. That...

653
01:07:14.238 --> 01:07:16.238
He's backing up
those sons-of-bitches.

654
01:07:16.273 --> 01:07:18.207
I know he is.

655
01:07:18.242 --> 01:07:20.605
Then why... Why do you ask me
to lay down to them. Mike?

656
01:07:26.844 --> 01:07:29.152
It was Hyman Roth
that tried to have me killed.

657
01:07:31.882 --> 01:07:33.486
I know it was him.

658
01:07:35.259 --> 01:07:36.423
Jesus Christ. Mike.

659
01:07:37.723 --> 01:07:39.591
Jesus Christ.
let's get them all.

660
01:07:39.626 --> 01:07:42.297
Let's get 'em all now.
while we got the muscle.

661
01:07:45.434 --> 01:07:47.533
(SIGHS)

662
01:07:47.568 --> 01:07:49.832
This used to be
my father's old study.

663
01:07:51.638 --> 01:07:53.341
It's changed.

664
01:07:55.213 --> 01:07:58.742
I remember
there used to be
a big desk here.

665
01:08:02.484 --> 01:08:04.253
I remember
when I was a kid. Frankie.

666
01:08:04.288 --> 01:08:06.222
We had to be quiet when
we played near here.

667
01:08:15.200 --> 01:08:17.827
I was very happy
that this house
never went to strangers.

668
01:08:20.337 --> 01:08:22.337
First Clemenza
took it over.

669
01:08:22.372 --> 01:08:23.668
Now you.

670
01:08:25.870 --> 01:08:28.607
My father taught me
many things here.

671
01:08:28.642 --> 01:08:30.279
He taught me in this room.

672
01:08:34.384 --> 01:08:38.254
He taught me.
"Keep your friends close.

673
01:08:38.289 --> 01:08:40.586
"but your enemies
closer."

674
01:08:40.621 --> 01:08:43.919
If Hyman Roth sees
that I interceded in this.

675
01:08:43.954 --> 01:08:46.856
in the Rosato brothers' favor.

676
01:08:46.891 --> 01:08:49.760
he'll think his relationship
with me is still good.

677
01:08:49.795 --> 01:08:51.894
(BOTH SPEAKING ITALIAN)

678
01:08:53.370 --> 01:08:54.699
That's what
I want him to think.

679
01:08:56.505 --> 01:09:01.277
I want him relaxed and
confident in our friendship.

680
01:09:01.312 --> 01:09:04.544
Then I'll be able to find out
who the traitor
in my family was.

681
01:09:09.716 --> 01:09:11.518
(PHONE RINGING)

682
01:09:13.720 --> 01:09:15.456
(PHONE RINGING)

683
01:09:17.691 --> 01:09:19.394
(PHONE RINGING)

684
01:09:21.926 --> 01:09:23.530
(PHONE RINGING)

685
01:09:26.601 --> 01:09:28.205
(HANDSET CLATTERING)

686
01:09:32.706 --> 01:09:34.706
Yeah?

687
01:09:34.741 --> 01:09:37.841
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Fredo. this is Johnny...</i>
<i>Johnny Ola.</i>

688
01:09:37.876 --> 01:09:39.612
<i>We need some more help.</i>

689
01:09:39.647 --> 01:09:41.746
Johnny?

690
01:09:41.781 --> 01:09:44.551
Jesus Christ.
what the hell time
is it?

691
01:09:44.586 --> 01:09:46.014
Who's that. honey?
(SHUSHING)

692
01:09:46.049 --> 01:09:47.719
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Listen good. Fredo.</i>

693
01:09:47.754 --> 01:09:49.424
Why are you
calling me here for?

694
01:09:49.459 --> 01:09:51.558
I don't want
to talk to you.

695
01:09:51.593 --> 01:09:53.824
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Pentangeli set up a meeting</i>
<i>with the Rosato brothers</i>

696
01:09:53.859 --> 01:09:55.496
<i>says he's gonna go</i>
<i>for their deal.</i>

697
01:09:55.531 --> 01:09:57.531
Oh. God.
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Will he come alone?</i>

698
01:09:57.566 --> 01:09:59.962
I don't know anything.
You've got me in
deep enough already.

699
01:09:59.997 --> 01:10:02.734
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Just go along. Everything</i>
<i>will be all right. Fredo.</i>

700
01:10:02.769 --> 01:10:05.605
<i>Pentangeli says</i>
<i>he's willing</i>
<i>to make the deal.</i>

701
01:10:05.640 --> 01:10:09.873
<i>All we want to know</i>
<i>is if he's on the level. or</i>
<i>if he's gonna bring his boys.</i>

702
01:10:09.908 --> 01:10:13.283
You lied to me.
I don't want you
to call me anymore.

703
01:10:13.318 --> 01:10:15.846
JOHNNY: (OVER PHONE)
<i>Your brother's not gonna</i>
<i>find out we talked.</i>

704
01:10:15.881 --> 01:10:17.749
I don't know what
you're talking about.

705
01:10:18.785 --> 01:10:20.521
(HANDSET CLATTERING)

706
01:10:22.426 --> 01:10:24.261
(SIGHS)

707
01:10:28.861 --> 01:10:30.663
Who was that?

708
01:10:30.698 --> 01:10:32.335
Uh. wrong number.

709
01:10:33.965 --> 01:10:35.833
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

710
01:10:39.806 --> 01:10:42.807
Frankie. I've got
nobody here.

711
01:10:42.842 --> 01:10:44.072
Wait in the car.
Cicc'.

712
01:10:44.107 --> 01:10:46.448
Frankie.
That's okay. Cicc'.

713
01:10:53.754 --> 01:10:55.358
What's this?

714
01:10:55.393 --> 01:10:57.492
A lucky C note
for our new deal.

715
01:11:00.695 --> 01:11:03.025
Ritchie.
Give us a taste.

716
01:11:08.032 --> 01:11:10.769
We were all real happy
about your decision. Frankie.

717
01:11:11.805 --> 01:11:13.541
You won't regret it.

718
01:11:13.576 --> 01:11:16.379
I don't like
the C note. Rosato.

719
01:11:16.414 --> 01:11:18.843
I take that
as an insult.

720
01:11:18.878 --> 01:11:21.076
(SCREAMING)
Michael Corleone
says hello!

721
01:11:21.111 --> 01:11:23.078
(GAGGING)

722
01:11:27.117 --> 01:11:30.360
(SCREAMING)

723
01:11:38.502 --> 01:11:41.602
BUTTON MAN: Get his head in.
TONY: Close the fuckin' door.

724
01:11:41.637 --> 01:11:43.835
Your friend the cop.
what the...

725
01:11:43.870 --> 01:11:46.706
Hey. Ritch.
It's dark in here.

726
01:11:46.741 --> 01:11:48.576
Are you open or closed?

727
01:11:48.611 --> 01:11:50.809
Hey. I just came in
to clean up a little.
you know?

728
01:11:54.683 --> 01:11:56.848
What's the matter?

729
01:11:56.883 --> 01:11:58.421
Is that something
on the floor?

730
01:11:58.456 --> 01:12:00.390
RITCH: Carmine.
not here! Not here!

731
01:12:00.425 --> 01:12:02.722
CARMINE: Anthony!
RITCH: Not here. Carmine.
let him go!

732
01:12:02.757 --> 01:12:04.592
(ALL CLAMORING)

733
01:12:04.627 --> 01:12:07.122
You open this fucking bar
and I'll blow your head in!

734
01:12:07.157 --> 01:12:09.091
(GUNS FIRING)

735
01:12:09.126 --> 01:12:11.797
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

736
01:12:27.111 --> 01:12:29.518
(TIRES SCREECHING)

737
01:12:30.719 --> 01:12:33.115
(ENGINE PUTTERING)

738
01:12:47.538 --> 01:12:49.032
(ENGINE STOPS)

739
01:12:54.204 --> 01:12:56.138
MAN: Freddy. it's good
to see you.

740
01:12:59.044 --> 01:13:00.813
How is he?

741
01:13:00.848 --> 01:13:03.585
He's okay.
He's in the back.

742
01:13:07.591 --> 01:13:09.624
Come on girls.
take a hike. eh.

743
01:13:13.025 --> 01:13:14.497
In this room here.

744
01:13:17.832 --> 01:13:19.535
I want to talk
to him alone first.

745
01:13:19.570 --> 01:13:21.064
Come on. eh.

746
01:13:25.972 --> 01:13:27.576
(DOOR CLOSING)

747
01:13:30.240 --> 01:13:31.910
I thought I could
help you. Senator.

748
01:13:36.950 --> 01:13:38.554
Hagen?

749
01:13:39.887 --> 01:13:42.118
Listen. Hagen. I did not...

750
01:13:42.153 --> 01:13:44.120
TOM: I know.
It's all right.

751
01:13:44.155 --> 01:13:46.221
I didn't do anything.
It's okay.

752
01:13:47.796 --> 01:13:49.862
You're very lucky.

753
01:13:49.897 --> 01:13:52.601
My brother Fredo
operates this place.

754
01:13:52.636 --> 01:13:55.637
He was called
before anyone.

755
01:13:55.672 --> 01:13:57.969
Had this happened
someplace else.
we couldn't have helped you.

756
01:14:00.611 --> 01:14:02.138
(EXHALES LOUDLY)

757
01:14:02.173 --> 01:14:04.481
When I woke up.
I was on the floor.

758
01:14:06.914 --> 01:14:08.881
And I don't know
how it happened.

759
01:14:08.916 --> 01:14:10.586
TOM: You can't
remember?

760
01:14:14.757 --> 01:14:16.493
I passed out.

761
01:14:22.831 --> 01:14:24.259
I...I'll fix it.

762
01:14:32.841 --> 01:14:36.645
(VOICE TREMBLING)
Just a game. Jesus.

763
01:14:36.680 --> 01:14:38.042
(SOBS)

764
01:14:46.657 --> 01:14:48.558
(SOBBING) Jesus. Jesus!

765
01:14:51.992 --> 01:14:53.222
(INAUDIBLE)

766
01:14:53.257 --> 01:14:56.291
GEARY: (SOBBING)
Jesus God! Oh. God!

767
01:15:00.231 --> 01:15:03.969
(STUTTERING) I don't know.
and I don't understand
why I can't remember.

768
01:15:04.004 --> 01:15:07.137
You don't have to remember.
just do as I say.

769
01:15:07.172 --> 01:15:09.744
We're putting a call
into your office.

770
01:15:09.779 --> 01:15:13.847
explain that you'll
be there tomorrow afternoon.

771
01:15:13.882 --> 01:15:18.313
You decided to spend the night
at Michael Corleone's house
in Tahoe...

772
01:15:18.348 --> 01:15:20.348
as his guest.

773
01:15:20.383 --> 01:15:22.955
I do remember
that she was laughing.

774
01:15:25.322 --> 01:15:27.256
We'd done it before.

775
01:15:27.291 --> 01:15:30.765
and I know that I could not
have hurt that girl.

776
01:15:31.933 --> 01:15:33.801
This girl has no family.

777
01:15:33.836 --> 01:15:36.001
Nobody knows
that she worked here.

778
01:15:36.036 --> 01:15:38.168
It'll be as though
she never existed.

779
01:15:41.305 --> 01:15:43.107
All that's left
is our friendship.

780
01:15:58.388 --> 01:16:00.256
KAY: Yes?

781
01:16:00.291 --> 01:16:03.732
I'm sorry. Mrs. Corleone.
we're not to let you through.

782
01:16:03.767 --> 01:16:05.195
I'm just going
to the market.

783
01:16:05.230 --> 01:16:06.394
Well. if you'll just
give us a list.

784
01:16:06.429 --> 01:16:07.967
we'll pick up anything
you want.

785
01:16:08.002 --> 01:16:09.639
Whose orders are these?

786
01:16:09.674 --> 01:16:11.773
Mr. Hagen's. ma'am.
He's coming over here now.

787
01:16:11.808 --> 01:16:14.743
All right. well.
I'm just goin' to have to
speak with Mr. Hagen.

788
01:16:20.014 --> 01:16:23.180
I wanted to explain.
but I had business
in Carson City.

789
01:16:23.215 --> 01:16:25.655
Now. this is Michael's request
for your safety.

790
01:16:25.690 --> 01:16:27.789
Now. we can send out
for anything you need.

791
01:16:27.824 --> 01:16:30.286
I see. So I'm supposed to
stay in my house?

792
01:16:30.321 --> 01:16:32.992
No. within the compound
will be fine.

793
01:16:33.027 --> 01:16:35.192
Tom. I was going to take
the children to
New England next week.

794
01:16:35.227 --> 01:16:36.963
That's off.

795
01:16:36.998 --> 01:16:38.800
KAY: Am I a prisoner?
Is that it?

796
01:16:38.835 --> 01:16:40.131
TOM: That's not the way
we look at it. Kay.

797
01:16:40.166 --> 01:16:41.396
KAY: All right. Come on. kids.

798
01:16:41.431 --> 01:16:43.002
We're going
back to the house.

799
01:16:45.809 --> 01:16:47.072
TOM: Joe.

800
01:17:33.351 --> 01:17:35.186
BOY: Cuba. Cuba!

801
01:17:53.910 --> 01:17:55.404
(KIDS CLAMORING)

802
01:18:05.515 --> 01:18:09.726
(BOY CHATTERING
IN SPANISH)

803
01:18:15.426 --> 01:18:17.327
PRESIDENT: Most respected
gentlemen.

804
01:18:17.362 --> 01:18:19.131
(TRANSLATOR REPEATS
IN SPANISH)

805
01:18:19.166 --> 01:18:21.331
PRESIDENT: Allow me to welcome
you to the city of Havana.

806
01:18:21.366 --> 01:18:23.498
(TRANSLATING)

807
01:18:23.533 --> 01:18:28.008
I want to thank
this distinguished group
of American industrialists

808
01:18:28.043 --> 01:18:30.373
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

809
01:18:30.408 --> 01:18:32.276
for continuing
to work with Cuba

810
01:18:32.311 --> 01:18:34.212
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

811
01:18:34.247 --> 01:18:36.412
for the greatest
period of prosperity

812
01:18:36.447 --> 01:18:38.183
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

813
01:18:38.218 --> 01:18:39.888
PRESIDENT:
...in her entire history.

814
01:18:39.923 --> 01:18:41.417
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

815
01:18:41.452 --> 01:18:43.452
PRESIDENT: Mr. William Shaw.
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

816
01:18:43.487 --> 01:18:45.487
PRESIDENT:...representing
the General Fruit Company.

817
01:18:45.522 --> 01:18:47.489
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

818
01:18:47.524 --> 01:18:50.261
PRESIDENT: Messrs.
Corngold and Dant.
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

819
01:18:50.296 --> 01:18:52.362
PRESIDENT:...of
United Telephone
and Telegraph Company.

820
01:18:52.397 --> 01:18:54.496
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

821
01:18:54.531 --> 01:18:56.806
PRESIDENT: Mr. Petty.

822
01:18:56.841 --> 01:18:59.303
Regional Vice President
of the Pan American
Mining Corporation.

823
01:18:59.338 --> 01:19:01.943
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

824
01:19:01.978 --> 01:19:04.176
PRESIDENT: Mr. Robert Allen
of South American Sugar.

825
01:19:04.211 --> 01:19:06.574
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

826
01:19:06.609 --> 01:19:08.543
PRESIDENT:
Mr. Michael Corleone
of Nevada.

827
01:19:08.578 --> 01:19:11.051
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

828
01:19:11.086 --> 01:19:13.581
PRESIDENT:...representing
our associates in tourism
and leisure activities.

829
01:19:13.616 --> 01:19:15.418
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

830
01:19:15.453 --> 01:19:18.157
PRESIDENT: And my old friend
and associate from Florida.

831
01:19:18.192 --> 01:19:20.423
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

832
01:19:20.458 --> 01:19:22.898
PRESIDENT: Mr. Hyman Roth.

833
01:19:22.933 --> 01:19:26.165
I would like to take
this opportunity to thank
United Telephone and Telegraph

834
01:19:26.200 --> 01:19:27.595
for their lovely
Christmas gift.

835
01:19:27.630 --> 01:19:30.532
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

836
01:19:33.108 --> 01:19:35.273
A solid gold telephone.

837
01:19:35.308 --> 01:19:37.572
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

838
01:19:37.607 --> 01:19:39.541
Perhaps you gentlemen
would like to look at it.

839
01:19:39.576 --> 01:19:41.950
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

840
01:19:41.985 --> 01:19:43.985
GUEST 1: Mr. President?
Yes?

841
01:19:44.020 --> 01:19:47.021
GUEST 1: Perhaps you
would discuss the status
of rebel activity

842
01:19:47.056 --> 01:19:49.452
and. uh. what this can mean
to our businesses?

843
01:19:49.487 --> 01:19:51.256
PRESIDENT: Of course.
Heavy stuff.

844
01:19:51.291 --> 01:19:53.929
PRESIDENT: I assure you that.
although the rebels

845
01:19:53.964 --> 01:19:57.196
have mounted an impressive
campaign in Las Villas.

846
01:19:57.231 --> 01:19:59.935
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

847
01:20:03.501 --> 01:20:05.633
PRESIDENT:...my staff
indicates. with assurance.

848
01:20:05.668 --> 01:20:09.241
that we'll drive them
out of the city of Santa Clara

849
01:20:09.276 --> 01:20:10.946
before the New Year.

850
01:20:10.981 --> 01:20:13.311
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

851
01:20:13.346 --> 01:20:14.917
PRESIDENT: And I want to
put you all at ease.

852
01:20:14.952 --> 01:20:17.117
(TRANSLATOR TRANSLATING)

853
01:20:17.152 --> 01:20:19.614
We will tolerate no guerrillas
in the casinos or
the swimming pools.

854
01:20:19.649 --> 01:20:21.550
(ALL LAUGHING)

855
01:20:21.585 --> 01:20:23.354
(CAR HONKING)

856
01:20:31.496 --> 01:20:34.365
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

857
01:20:38.602 --> 01:20:41.108
He said that
they're making an arrest.

858
01:20:41.143 --> 01:20:44.177
and in a few minutes
he'll let us through.

859
01:20:44.212 --> 01:20:45.475
Johnny...

860
01:20:45.510 --> 01:20:48.115
(SPEAKING IN ITALIAN)

861
01:20:49.712 --> 01:20:52.449
(REBEL SHOUTING
IN SPANISH)

862
01:20:52.484 --> 01:20:54.187
<i>Viva Fidel!</i>

863
01:20:54.222 --> 01:20:56.651
(CAR HORN BLARING)

864
01:21:06.135 --> 01:21:07.596
(EXCLAIMS)

865
01:21:09.974 --> 01:21:12.073
I hope my age
is correct.

866
01:21:12.108 --> 01:21:15.978
I'm always accurate
about my age.

867
01:21:16.013 --> 01:21:19.949
Make sure that everybody
sees the cake
before we cut it.

868
01:21:19.984 --> 01:21:21.313
(CLEARS THROAT)

869
01:21:22.646 --> 01:21:25.449
I'm very pleased

870
01:21:25.484 --> 01:21:29.552
you're all able to come
from such distances
to be with me today.

871
01:21:31.523 --> 01:21:34.095
When a man comes
to this point
in his life.

872
01:21:35.692 --> 01:21:39.364
he wants to
turn over the things
he's been blessed with.

873
01:21:39.399 --> 01:21:44.534
Turn them over to friends.
as a reward for
the friends he's had

874
01:21:45.669 --> 01:21:47.504
and to make sure

875
01:21:47.539 --> 01:21:51.046
that everything goes well
after he's gone.

876
01:21:51.081 --> 01:21:52.410
Not for years.

877
01:21:52.445 --> 01:21:54.544
GUESTS: Hear. hear!

878
01:21:54.579 --> 01:21:57.481
Well. we'll see.
The doctors would disagree.
but what do they know?

879
01:21:59.353 --> 01:22:04.257
These are wonderful things
that we've achieved in Havana

880
01:22:04.292 --> 01:22:07.458
and there's no limit
to where we can go from here.

881
01:22:07.493 --> 01:22:12.298
This kind of government
knows how to help business.
to encourage it.

882
01:22:12.333 --> 01:22:16.500
The hotels here
are bigger and swankier

883
01:22:16.535 --> 01:22:19.437
than any of the rug joints
in Vegas.

884
01:22:19.472 --> 01:22:22.506
We can thank our friends
in the Cuban government

885
01:22:22.541 --> 01:22:27.379
which has put up half the cash
with the Teamsters.
on a dollar for dollar basis

886
01:22:27.414 --> 01:22:30.283
and has relaxed
restrictions on imports.

887
01:22:30.318 --> 01:22:32.318
What I'm saying is
that we have now

888
01:22:32.353 --> 01:22:34.749
what we have
always needed...

889
01:22:34.784 --> 01:22:37.752
Real partnership
with a government.

890
01:22:37.787 --> 01:22:39.325
Smaller piece.

891
01:22:40.493 --> 01:22:43.164
You all know
Michael Corleone

892
01:22:43.199 --> 01:22:45.430
and we all remember
his father.

893
01:22:45.465 --> 01:22:47.465
At the time
of my retirement.

894
01:22:47.500 --> 01:22:49.203
or death.

895
01:22:49.238 --> 01:22:53.141
I turn over all my interests
in the Havana operation

896
01:22:53.176 --> 01:22:55.209
to his control.
<i>Grazie.</i>

897
01:22:55.244 --> 01:22:59.312
But. all of you
will share.

898
01:22:59.347 --> 01:23:03.184
The Nacionale will go
to the Lakeville Road Boys.

899
01:23:03.219 --> 01:23:06.451
the Capri to
the Corleone family.

900
01:23:06.486 --> 01:23:09.223
the Sevilla Biltmore also.

901
01:23:09.258 --> 01:23:12.754
but Eddie Levine
will bring in the
Pennino brothers.

902
01:23:12.789 --> 01:23:15.229
Dino and Eddie. for a piece

903
01:23:15.264 --> 01:23:17.759
and to handle
the actual casino operations.

904
01:23:17.794 --> 01:23:21.400
And we've saved a piece
for some friends
in Nevada

905
01:23:21.435 --> 01:23:24.205
to make sure that things
go smoothly back home.

906
01:23:25.868 --> 01:23:27.373
Uh...

907
01:23:27.408 --> 01:23:30.343
I want all of you
to enjoy your cake.

908
01:23:30.378 --> 01:23:32.510
So. enjoy!

909
01:23:32.545 --> 01:23:33.709
GUESTS: Happy birthday!

910
01:23:33.744 --> 01:23:36.118
<i>L'chaim!</i>

911
01:23:36.153 --> 01:23:37.746
I saw an interesting thing
happen today.

912
01:23:40.190 --> 01:23:43.488
A rebel was being arrested
by the military police.

913
01:23:43.523 --> 01:23:47.855
Rather than be taken alive.
he exploded a grenade
he had hidden in his jacket.

914
01:23:47.890 --> 01:23:51.463
He killed himself
and took a captain
of the command with him.

915
01:23:51.498 --> 01:23:54.598
Right Johnny?
JOHNNY: Those rebels.
you know. they're lunatics.

916
01:23:54.633 --> 01:23:57.139
Maybe so.

917
01:23:57.174 --> 01:24:00.505
But it occurred to me.
that the soldiers
are paid to fight.

918
01:24:00.540 --> 01:24:02.177
the rebels aren't.

919
01:24:02.212 --> 01:24:03.541
What does that
tell you?

920
01:24:04.676 --> 01:24:06.313
They can win.

921
01:24:08.251 --> 01:24:11.153
This country
has had rebels
for 50 years.

922
01:24:11.188 --> 01:24:12.880
It's in their blood.
Believe me I know.

923
01:24:12.915 --> 01:24:15.817
I've been coming here
since the '20s.

924
01:24:15.852 --> 01:24:19.722
We were running
molasses from Havana
when you were a baby.

925
01:24:19.757 --> 01:24:22.230
The trucks.
owned by your father.

926
01:24:23.464 --> 01:24:25.101
Michael.

927
01:24:32.341 --> 01:24:34.572
I'd rather we
talked about this
when we're alone.

928
01:24:38.215 --> 01:24:40.281
The two million
never got to the island.

929
01:24:46.784 --> 01:24:50.159
I wouldn't want it to
get around that you
held back the money

930
01:24:50.194 --> 01:24:51.886
because you had second
thoughts about the rebels.

931
01:24:58.796 --> 01:25:02.468
Ah. sit down. Michael.
Sit down.

932
01:25:05.308 --> 01:25:07.209
(SIGHS)

933
01:25:10.313 --> 01:25:13.809
If I could only live
to see it. to be there
with you.

934
01:25:13.844 --> 01:25:16.416
(EXCLAIMS LONGINGLY)

935
01:25:16.451 --> 01:25:20.651
What I wouldn't give
for 20 more years.

936
01:25:22.457 --> 01:25:25.260
Here we are. protected.

937
01:25:25.295 --> 01:25:26.888
Free to make our profits
without Kefauver.

938
01:25:26.923 --> 01:25:31.431
the goddamn
Justice Department
and the FBI.

939
01:25:31.466 --> 01:25:34.764
Ninety miles away.
in partnership
with a friendly government.

940
01:25:36.240 --> 01:25:38.339
Ninety miles.

941
01:25:38.374 --> 01:25:40.374
It's nothing.

942
01:25:40.409 --> 01:25:42.442
Just one small step

943
01:25:42.477 --> 01:25:46.446
looking for a man
that wants to be
President of the United States

944
01:25:46.481 --> 01:25:48.580
and having the cash
to make it possible.

945
01:25:49.748 --> 01:25:51.385
Michael.

946
01:25:53.455 --> 01:25:55.752
we're bigger
than U.S. Steel.

947
01:26:22.418 --> 01:26:24.550
Mikey. how are you?
Okay?

948
01:26:26.719 --> 01:26:29.687
Hi! Uh. Freddie Corleone.

949
01:26:29.722 --> 01:26:31.392
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

950
01:26:32.626 --> 01:26:35.022
Jesus Christ.
what a trip!

951
01:26:35.057 --> 01:26:38.696
The whole time I'm thinkin'
"What if somebody knows
what I've got in here".

952
01:26:38.731 --> 01:26:40.500
Can you imagine that. huh?

953
01:26:40.535 --> 01:26:42.865
Two million dollars on the
seat next to me in the plane.

954
01:26:46.706 --> 01:26:48.277
Whoa. Excuse me.

955
01:26:48.312 --> 01:26:49.806
No. It's okay.

956
01:26:51.480 --> 01:26:53.315
You want to
count it?

957
01:26:57.816 --> 01:26:59.717
Mikey. what the hell
is going on anyway?

958
01:26:59.752 --> 01:27:01.389
I'm totally
in the dark.

959
01:27:01.424 --> 01:27:03.688
The family is making
an investment in Havana.

960
01:27:03.723 --> 01:27:06.955
This is a little gift
for the President.
Oh.

961
01:27:06.990 --> 01:27:09.056
(SIRENS WAILING IN A DISTANCE)
Well. that's great!

962
01:27:09.091 --> 01:27:10.563
Havana's great.

963
01:27:12.402 --> 01:27:13.698
It's my kind of town.

964
01:27:15.570 --> 01:27:17.504
Anybody I know
in Havana?

965
01:27:17.539 --> 01:27:20.573
Don't know.
Hyman Roth. Johnny Ola?

966
01:27:20.608 --> 01:27:23.312
(SIRENS WAILING)

967
01:27:23.347 --> 01:27:25.842
(QUIETLY) No.
No. I've never met them.

968
01:27:29.716 --> 01:27:32.948
Listen. Mikey.
I'm. uh... I'm kind of...

969
01:27:37.526 --> 01:27:39.020
Kind of nervous
from the trip.

970
01:27:39.055 --> 01:27:42.727
(STUTTERING)
Can I get a drink
or something?

971
01:27:42.762 --> 01:27:46.060
I thought maybe
we'd go out together.

972
01:27:46.095 --> 01:27:48.634
I know a place
where we can spend
some time together. Okay?

973
01:27:51.573 --> 01:27:53.672
Sometimes I think
I should have married
a woman like you did.

974
01:27:54.774 --> 01:27:57.071
Like Kay.

975
01:27:57.106 --> 01:27:59.645
Have kids.
Have a family.

976
01:28:02.386 --> 01:28:07.015
For once in my life.
be more like...

977
01:28:07.050 --> 01:28:09.556
Pop.

978
01:28:09.591 --> 01:28:11.019
(SPANISH SONG PLAYING)

979
01:28:11.054 --> 01:28:14.088
It's not easy
to be a son. Fredo.

980
01:28:14.123 --> 01:28:15.661
It's not easy.

981
01:28:15.696 --> 01:28:16.992
You know Mama
used to tease me.

982
01:28:17.027 --> 01:28:18.895
She'd say. uh.
"You don't belong to me."

983
01:28:18.930 --> 01:28:21.502
"You were left
on the doorstep
by gypsies."

984
01:28:22.769 --> 01:28:24.637
Sometimes
I think it's true.

985
01:28:25.739 --> 01:28:27.574
You're no gypsy.
Fredo.

986
01:28:29.105 --> 01:28:32.579
Mikey. I was
mad at you.

987
01:28:40.754 --> 01:28:42.688
Why didn't we spend
time like this before?

988
01:28:44.494 --> 01:28:46.956
You want a drink.
right? Waiter!

989
01:28:50.192 --> 01:28:52.401
Uh...<i> Por favor...</i>

990
01:28:54.570 --> 01:28:56.405
How do you say
Banana Daiquiri?

991
01:28:56.440 --> 01:28:57.835
Banana Daiquiri.

992
01:28:57.870 --> 01:28:59.870
That's it?
That's it.

993
01:28:59.905 --> 01:29:02.906
<i>Uno</i> Banana Daiquiri
WAITER: Banana Daiquiri.
<i>si senor</i>

994
01:29:02.941 --> 01:29:05.480
and. uh. a club soda.

995
01:29:13.490 --> 01:29:16.084
Senator Geary flies in
from Washington tomorrow night

996
01:29:16.119 --> 01:29:18.625
with some people.
some government people.

997
01:29:18.660 --> 01:29:20.858
I want you to show them
a good time in Havana.

998
01:29:24.468 --> 01:29:26.699
That's my specialty.
right?

999
01:29:26.734 --> 01:29:28.800
Can I trust you
with something. Fredo?

1000
01:29:28.835 --> 01:29:29.966
Of course. Mike.

1001
01:29:33.675 --> 01:29:37.743
Later on in the evening
we're all invited to the
Presidential Palace reception

1002
01:29:37.778 --> 01:29:39.910
to bring in the New Year.

1003
01:29:39.945 --> 01:29:41.714
After it's over

1004
01:29:41.749 --> 01:29:45.520
they'll take me home
in a military car. alone.

1005
01:29:45.555 --> 01:29:48.083
For my protection.

1006
01:29:48.118 --> 01:29:50.217
Before I reach my hotel.

1007
01:29:50.252 --> 01:29:52.153
I'll be assassinated.

1008
01:30:09.876 --> 01:30:11.711
Who?

1009
01:30:11.746 --> 01:30:13.075
Roth.

1010
01:30:18.687 --> 01:30:21.050
It was Roth who
tried to kill me
in my home.

1011
01:30:23.593 --> 01:30:25.989
It was Roth
all along.

1012
01:30:26.024 --> 01:30:29.531
He acts like I'm his son.
his successor.

1013
01:30:31.260 --> 01:30:33.931
But he thinks
he'll live forever
and wants me out.

1014
01:30:38.938 --> 01:30:40.641
How can I help?

1015
01:30:40.676 --> 01:30:42.610
Just go along.
as if you know nothing.

1016
01:30:43.778 --> 01:30:45.646
I've already made
my move.

1017
01:30:45.681 --> 01:30:47.714
What move?

1018
01:30:47.749 --> 01:30:49.848
Hyman Roth won't
see the New Year.

1019
01:31:01.191 --> 01:31:03.928
(DOCTOR SPEAKING SPANISH)

1020
01:31:07.296 --> 01:31:09.296
Says you have to
take it easy.

1021
01:31:09.331 --> 01:31:11.540
And he's gonna
give you a prescription.
He'll be back tomorrow.

1022
01:31:11.575 --> 01:31:13.971
I want my own doctor.
Fly him in from Miami.

1023
01:31:14.006 --> 01:31:16.072
I don't trust a doctor
who can't speak English.

1024
01:31:18.010 --> 01:31:19.306
WOMAN:<i> Gracias. senor.</i>

1025
01:31:19.341 --> 01:31:21.011
DOCTOR:<i> Buenas noches.</i>

1026
01:31:22.817 --> 01:31:24.751
Honey. go down to the casino.

1027
01:31:24.786 --> 01:31:26.621
Well. if you're sure
you're feeling better.

1028
01:31:26.656 --> 01:31:28.216
Feel fine.
(KISSES)

1029
01:31:30.022 --> 01:31:31.252
Play the
bingo game.

1030
01:31:31.287 --> 01:31:32.957
Okay. Nice to see you.
Mr. Paul.

1031
01:31:32.992 --> 01:31:34.255
Just make yourself
at home.

1032
01:31:36.963 --> 01:31:40.998
My sixth sense tells me
your brother Fredo brought
a bag full of money.

1033
01:31:41.033 --> 01:31:42.263
Where is it?

1034
01:31:44.201 --> 01:31:45.706
You're pulling out?

1035
01:31:46.907 --> 01:31:48.610
Just want to...

1036
01:31:49.646 --> 01:31:50.777
I just want to wait.

1037
01:31:54.244 --> 01:31:56.013
MICHAEL:
How do you feel?

1038
01:31:56.048 --> 01:31:58.246
(SCOFFS) Terrible.

1039
01:31:58.281 --> 01:32:02.283
I'd give four million
to be able to take
a piss without it hurting.

1040
01:32:02.318 --> 01:32:04.285
Who had
Frank Pentangeli killed?

1041
01:32:05.926 --> 01:32:08.124
The...Rosato brothers.

1042
01:32:08.159 --> 01:32:09.829
MICHAEL: I know.

1043
01:32:09.864 --> 01:32:12.260
but who gave
the go-ahead?

1044
01:32:12.295 --> 01:32:13.767
I know I didn't.

1045
01:32:21.975 --> 01:32:24.679
There was this kid
I grew up with.

1046
01:32:24.714 --> 01:32:27.011
He was younger
than me.

1047
01:32:27.046 --> 01:32:29.684
Sort of looked up
to me. you know.

1048
01:32:29.719 --> 01:32:33.182
We did our
first work together.

1049
01:32:33.217 --> 01:32:35.316
Worked our way
out of the street.

1050
01:32:35.351 --> 01:32:37.626
Things were good.
We made the most of it.

1051
01:32:37.661 --> 01:32:43.291
During Prohibition
we ran molasses
into Canada.

1052
01:32:43.326 --> 01:32:45.766
Made a fortune.
Your father. too.

1053
01:32:48.331 --> 01:32:50.067
As much as anyone.

1054
01:32:51.301 --> 01:32:54.137
I loved him
and trusted him.

1055
01:32:57.076 --> 01:32:59.780
Later on
he had an idea

1056
01:33:00.882 --> 01:33:02.915
to build a city

1057
01:33:02.950 --> 01:33:06.622
out of a desert stop-over
for G.I.s on the way
to the West Coast.

1058
01:33:08.824 --> 01:33:11.121
That kid's name
was Moe Greene

1059
01:33:12.729 --> 01:33:16.291
and the city he invented
was Las Vegas.

1060
01:33:17.327 --> 01:33:18.964
This was a great man.

1061
01:33:20.099 --> 01:33:22.836
A man of vision and guts.

1062
01:33:22.871 --> 01:33:26.136
And there isn't even
a plaque. or a signpost

1063
01:33:26.171 --> 01:33:28.974
or statue of him
in that town.

1064
01:33:31.077 --> 01:33:34.815
Someone put a bullet
through his eye.

1065
01:33:35.950 --> 01:33:39.182
No one knows
who gave the order.

1066
01:33:39.217 --> 01:33:42.350
When I heard it.
I wasn't angry.

1067
01:33:42.385 --> 01:33:44.451
I knew Moe.
I knew he was headstrong.

1068
01:33:44.486 --> 01:33:47.157
Talking loud.
saying stupid things.

1069
01:33:48.391 --> 01:33:50.061
So when he
turned up dead.

1070
01:33:51.999 --> 01:33:53.394
I let it go.

1071
01:33:55.200 --> 01:33:57.101
And I said to myself.

1072
01:33:57.136 --> 01:33:58.465
(SNAPS FINGERS)

1073
01:33:58.500 --> 01:34:02.304
"This is the business
we've chosen."

1074
01:34:02.339 --> 01:34:03.976
I didn't ask

1075
01:34:05.342 --> 01:34:07.309
who gave the order.

1076
01:34:07.344 --> 01:34:10.686
because it had nothing
to do with business.

1077
01:34:19.158 --> 01:34:23.028
That two million
in a bag in your room...

1078
01:34:25.967 --> 01:34:28.902
I'm going in
to take a nap.

1079
01:34:30.202 --> 01:34:32.202
When I wake.

1080
01:34:32.237 --> 01:34:33.775
if the money is
on the table.

1081
01:34:33.810 --> 01:34:36.074
I'll know I have a partner

1082
01:34:36.109 --> 01:34:38.274
If it isn't.
I'll know I don't.

1083
01:34:57.229 --> 01:35:01.000
(SHOW MUSIC PLAYING)

1084
01:35:07.206 --> 01:35:11.274
(MAN ANNOUNCING
IN SPANISH OVER P.A.)

1085
01:35:17.381 --> 01:35:19.480
(SINGING IN SPANISH)

1086
01:35:34.233 --> 01:35:36.332
All right does everybody know
everybody here. huh?

1087
01:35:36.367 --> 01:35:38.400
This is Senator Geary.
you know him.
How are you. Senator?

1088
01:35:38.435 --> 01:35:40.072
Good to see you. Mike.

1089
01:35:40.107 --> 01:35:42.206
I'm glad we could
spend this time together.

1090
01:35:42.241 --> 01:35:44.846
Right. this is Senator Payton
from Florida...
How you doing. Mike?

1091
01:35:44.881 --> 01:35:46.309
This is Judge DeMalco
from New York...

1092
01:35:46.344 --> 01:35:48.113
How do you do. sir?
Fine. thank you.

1093
01:35:48.148 --> 01:35:50.049
Right...Senator Ream
from Maryland...

1094
01:35:50.084 --> 01:35:51.479
REEVES: Mike. I've been
looking forward to it.

1095
01:35:51.514 --> 01:35:53.855
Fred Corngold from UTT.

1096
01:35:53.890 --> 01:35:56.517
That Freddie does a mean
cha-cha-cha
so watch out later.

1097
01:35:56.552 --> 01:35:58.123
MICHAEL: Oh he does. huh?

1098
01:35:58.158 --> 01:36:00.356
All right. gentlemen.
it's refill time here!

1099
01:36:00.391 --> 01:36:02.424
You might try some
of the local drinks. you know.

1100
01:36:02.459 --> 01:36:04.899
Cuba Libre...
Pina Colada...

1101
01:36:04.934 --> 01:36:08.837
I think I'll try
one of those...
redheaded Yolandas.

1102
01:36:08.872 --> 01:36:11.202
That you got!
<i>Con gusto...</i>

1103
01:36:11.237 --> 01:36:12.973
MICHAEL: Johnny!

1104
01:36:13.008 --> 01:36:14.876
You don't know my brother
Fredo. do you. Johnny?

1105
01:36:14.911 --> 01:36:16.438
Johnny Ola. Fredo.

1106
01:36:16.473 --> 01:36:18.539
We never met.
Johnny Ola.

1107
01:36:18.574 --> 01:36:20.277
Pleasure.

1108
01:36:21.643 --> 01:36:24.083
Gentlemen.
to a night
in Havana!

1109
01:36:24.118 --> 01:36:25.854
Happy New Year!
MAN 1: Happy New Year!

1110
01:36:25.889 --> 01:36:28.252
FREDO:
<i>Feliz Ano Nuevo!</i>
<i>Happy New Year.</i>

1111
01:36:28.287 --> 01:36:29.858
FREDO: Right. huh?

1112
01:36:31.059 --> 01:36:32.861
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1113
01:36:34.029 --> 01:36:35.358
FREDO: Okay. get in there.

1114
01:36:35.393 --> 01:36:37.932
GEARY: Never fear.
Pat Geary is here.

1115
01:36:37.967 --> 01:36:39.560
(SLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

1116
01:36:39.595 --> 01:36:42.904
GEARY: Hey! Hey. Freddy
why are we standing?

1117
01:36:42.939 --> 01:36:45.269
Everybody stands.
But it's worth it.

1118
01:36:45.304 --> 01:36:47.403
Watch. You're not gonna
believe this.

1119
01:36:47.438 --> 01:36:49.108
GEARY: I don't
believe it already.

1120
01:36:49.143 --> 01:36:50.472
FREDO: Huh?
Fifty dollars. right?

1121
01:36:50.507 --> 01:36:52.177
GEARY: You've got
a bet. mister.

1122
01:36:53.477 --> 01:36:55.345
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

1123
01:37:00.088 --> 01:37:02.187
(CROWD APPLAUDS)
That's him.
That's Superman.

1124
01:37:35.552 --> 01:37:37.959
(CROWD EXCLAIMING)
Did I tell you
or did I tell you?

1125
01:37:40.161 --> 01:37:41.556
GEARY: I don't
believe it!

1126
01:37:41.591 --> 01:37:42.931
That thing's
gotta be a fake.

1127
01:37:42.966 --> 01:37:44.163
That ain't no fake.
that's real.

1128
01:37:44.198 --> 01:37:46.660
That's why they
call him Superman.

1129
01:37:46.695 --> 01:37:50.631
GEARY: Hey. Freddy.
Freddy. where did you
find this place?

1130
01:37:50.666 --> 01:37:53.436
Johnny Ola told me
about this place.
He brought me here.

1131
01:37:53.471 --> 01:37:55.471
I didn't believe him.
but seeing is believing. huh!

1132
01:37:55.506 --> 01:37:57.638
GEARY: I see it.
but still don't
believe it!

1133
01:37:57.673 --> 01:37:59.112
FREDO: Fifty bucks. Pat.

1134
01:37:59.147 --> 01:38:01.081
Old man Roth would
never come here.

1135
01:38:01.116 --> 01:38:03.413
but Old Johnny
knows these places
like the back of his hand!

1136
01:38:03.448 --> 01:38:05.448
Now watch him.
he's gonna break
the cracker with it.

1137
01:38:05.483 --> 01:38:07.615
GEARY: Break a cracker...
I want to see him
break a brick.

1138
01:38:07.650 --> 01:38:09.683
(LAUGHING)

1139
01:38:09.718 --> 01:38:12.158
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1140
01:38:39.649 --> 01:38:41.187
(GASPS)

1141
01:38:45.127 --> 01:38:46.555
(GRUNTS)

1142
01:38:46.590 --> 01:38:48.326
(SIREN WAILING)

1143
01:39:30.832 --> 01:39:33.305
Relax.<i> Senor</i> Roth.
we're taking you
to the hospital.

1144
01:39:35.078 --> 01:39:36.374
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

1145
01:39:38.477 --> 01:39:41.247
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)
(DOOR OPENING)

1146
01:40:06.637 --> 01:40:09.506
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1147
01:40:22.884 --> 01:40:25.357
GEARY:...and in my judgment
you'll continue to get those

1148
01:40:25.392 --> 01:40:29.658
because I don't believe that
President Eisenhower would
ever pull out of Cuba...

1149
01:40:29.693 --> 01:40:33.596
Not as we have over
one billion dollars
invested in this country.

1150
01:40:36.733 --> 01:40:40.438
Now. the American public
believe in
non-intervention...

1151
01:40:40.473 --> 01:40:43.474
Fredo!
Where are you going?

1152
01:40:43.509 --> 01:40:45.674
I'm getting a real drink.
because I can't...

1153
01:41:26.189 --> 01:41:27.782
(MAN GROANING)

1154
01:41:35.429 --> 01:41:37.462
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1155
01:41:42.865 --> 01:41:46.504
What kept Mr. Roth?
I understood he was coming.

1156
01:41:46.539 --> 01:41:48.308
Hey. Reeves.
what's the protocol?

1157
01:41:48.343 --> 01:41:49.738
How long should we
stay around?

1158
01:41:49.773 --> 01:41:51.509
REEVES: Oh. I don't know.

1159
01:41:51.544 --> 01:41:53.346
I think a half hour
ought to do it.

1160
01:41:53.381 --> 01:41:55.282
Just long enough to
bring in the New Year.

1161
01:42:07.263 --> 01:42:10.462
(NURSES CHATTERING)

1162
01:42:10.497 --> 01:42:11.793
(SHUSHING)

1163
01:42:11.828 --> 01:42:15.236
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

1164
01:42:27.811 --> 01:42:30.779
(CHAMPAGNE CORK
POPPING)
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1165
01:43:01.944 --> 01:43:03.317
(SHRIEKS)

1166
01:43:09.017 --> 01:43:11.391
(PEOPLE CHEERING)

1167
01:43:11.426 --> 01:43:13.888
(MUSIC PLAYING)

1168
01:43:29.906 --> 01:43:34.348
(SOFTLY) There's a plane
waiting to take us
to Miami in an hour.

1169
01:43:34.383 --> 01:43:36.009
Don't make a big thing
about it.

1170
01:43:40.521 --> 01:43:42.752
I know it was
you. Fredo.

1171
01:43:42.787 --> 01:43:45.755
You broke my heart.

1172
01:43:45.790 --> 01:43:47.361
(WHISPERING FIERCELY)
You broke my heart!

1173
01:43:52.665 --> 01:43:54.797
(PEOPLE EXCLAIMING. CHEERING)

1174
01:44:19.593 --> 01:44:21.593
(MAN SHOUTING IN SPANISH)

1175
01:44:27.799 --> 01:44:29.898
(IN SPANISH)

1176
01:45:00.832 --> 01:45:04.867
<i>Salud! Salud! Salud!</i>

1177
01:45:04.902 --> 01:45:08.838
(MAN ON MEGAPHONE
SPEAKING SPANISH)

1178
01:45:08.873 --> 01:45:11.742
(EXPLOSION)
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

1179
01:45:19.983 --> 01:45:22.016
(CAR HONKING)

1180
01:45:23.085 --> 01:45:26.460
(SIREN WAILING)

1181
01:45:29.960 --> 01:45:32.433
MICHAEL: Fredo!

1182
01:45:32.468 --> 01:45:34.666
Come on.
Come with me.

1183
01:45:34.701 --> 01:45:36.899
It's the only way
out of here tonight.

1184
01:45:36.934 --> 01:45:39.704
Roth is dead. Fredo...

1185
01:45:39.739 --> 01:45:41.409
Fredo. come with me!

1186
01:45:41.444 --> 01:45:43.543
You're still my brother.
Fredo!

1187
01:45:45.008 --> 01:45:46.711
Fredo!

1188
01:45:46.746 --> 01:45:48.108
(TIRES SCREECHING)

1189
01:45:52.884 --> 01:45:55.555
(MAN ON MEGAPHONE
ANNOUNCING IN SPANISH)

1190
01:46:10.968 --> 01:46:12.770
I'm Pat Geary.
United States Senator.

1191
01:46:14.070 --> 01:46:16.037
(CHANTING SLOGANS IN SPANISH)

1192
01:46:37.027 --> 01:46:40.127
(MAN ON MEGAPHONE
CHANTING SLOGANS IN SPANISH)

1193
01:46:40.162 --> 01:46:41.898
(CROWD CHEERING)

1194
01:46:45.035 --> 01:46:47.068
CROWD: (CHANTING)
Fidel! Fidel! Fidel!

1195
01:47:27.176 --> 01:47:30.078
Al. Get me
a wet towel.

1196
01:47:37.219 --> 01:47:38.823
Kay know I'm back?

1197
01:47:43.962 --> 01:47:45.291
What about my boy?

1198
01:47:45.326 --> 01:47:47.535
Did you get him
something for Christmas?

1199
01:47:47.570 --> 01:47:48.965
I took care of it.

1200
01:47:49.000 --> 01:47:51.099
What was it.
so I'll know.

1201
01:47:51.134 --> 01:47:54.575
Well. it was a little car
with an electric motor
that he can ride in.

1202
01:47:54.610 --> 01:47:55.840
It's nice.

1203
01:47:58.713 --> 01:47:59.976
Thank you. Al.

1204
01:48:01.848 --> 01:48:04.145
Fellows.
could you step outside
for a minute please?

1205
01:48:22.198 --> 01:48:24.836
Where's my brother?
Uh...

1206
01:48:24.871 --> 01:48:28.103
Roth got out
on a private boat.
He's in a hospital in Miami.

1207
01:48:28.138 --> 01:48:29.841
He had a stroke.
but recovered okay.

1208
01:48:31.273 --> 01:48:33.075
