1413
02:24:01.170 --> 02:24:04.204
<i>No. No. I'm going to</i>
<i>allow Mr. Corleone</i>
<i>to read his statement.</i>

1414
02:24:04.239 --> 02:24:06.074
<i>I'll put it in the record.</i>

1415
02:24:07.979 --> 02:24:11.013
<i>In the hopes of clearing</i>
<i>my family name</i>

1416
02:24:11.048 --> 02:24:12.949
<i>and in the sincere desire to</i>
<i>give my children</i>

1417
02:24:12.984 --> 02:24:15.149
<i>their fair share</i>
<i>of the American way of life.</i>

1418
02:24:15.184 --> 02:24:18.218
<i>without a blemish</i>
<i>on their name</i>
<i>and background.</i>

1419
02:24:18.253 --> 02:24:20.385
<i>I have appeared</i>
<i>before this committee</i>

1420
02:24:20.420 --> 02:24:22.926
<i>and given it all the</i>
<i>cooperation in my power.</i>

1421
02:24:24.963 --> 02:24:27.832
<i>I consider it</i>
<i>a great dishonor</i>
<i>to me personally</i>

1422
02:24:27.867 --> 02:24:29.460
<i>to have to deny</i>
<i>that I am a criminal.</i>

1423
02:24:31.398 --> 02:24:34.971
<i>I wish to have the following</i>
<i>noted for the record...</i>

1424
02:24:35.006 --> 02:24:39.107
<i>That I served my country</i>
<i>faithfully and honorably</i>
<i>in World War Two</i>

1425
02:24:39.142 --> 02:24:41.439
<i>and was awarded</i>
<i>the Navy Cross</i>

1426
02:24:41.474 --> 02:24:45.113
<i>for actions in defense</i>
<i>of my country.</i>

1427
02:24:45.148 --> 02:24:49.447
<i>That I have never been</i>
<i>arrested or indicted</i>
<i>for any crime what-so-ever.</i>

1428
02:24:49.482 --> 02:24:53.451
<i>That no proof linking me</i>
<i>to any criminal conspiracy</i>

1429
02:24:53.486 --> 02:24:56.223
<i>whether it is called Mafia</i>
<i>or Cosa Nostra</i>

1430
02:24:56.258 --> 02:24:58.489
<i>or whatever other name</i>
<i>you wish to give</i>

1431
02:24:58.524 --> 02:25:01.063
<i>has ever</i>
<i>been made public.</i>

1432
02:25:01.098 --> 02:25:04.066
<i>I have not taken refuge</i>
<i>behind the Fifth Amendment.</i>

1433
02:25:04.101 --> 02:25:06.464
<i>although it's my right</i>
<i>to do so.</i>

1434
02:25:09.238 --> 02:25:11.172
<i>I challenge this committee</i>

1435
02:25:11.207 --> 02:25:14.945
<i>to produce any witness</i>
<i>or evidence against me</i>

1436
02:25:14.980 --> 02:25:17.343
<i>and if they do not.</i>

1437
02:25:17.378 --> 02:25:20.918
<i>I hope</i>
<i>they will have the decency</i>
<i>to clear my name</i>

1438
02:25:20.953 --> 02:25:26.253
<i>with the same publicity</i>
<i>with which they have</i>
<i>besmirched it.</i>

1439
02:25:26.288 --> 02:25:28.794
CHAIRMAN:<i> I'm sure</i>
<i>we're all quite impressed.</i>
<i>Mr. Corleone.</i>

1440
02:25:28.829 --> 02:25:31.522
<i>Particularly with your love</i>
<i>for our country.</i>

1441
02:25:31.557 --> 02:25:34.426
<i>The committee will stand</i>
<i>in recess until 10 A.M.</i>
<i>Monday morning.</i>

1442
02:25:34.461 --> 02:25:36.395
<i>when we will</i>
<i>produce a witness</i>

1443
02:25:36.430 --> 02:25:39.266
<i>who'll corroborate</i>
<i>the charges that are made</i>
<i>against you today.</i>

1444
02:25:39.301 --> 02:25:42.137
<i>At which time. Mr. Corleone.</i>
<i>you may very well be</i>

1445
02:25:42.172 --> 02:25:44.502
<i>subject to indictment</i>
<i>for perjury.</i>

1446
02:25:44.537 --> 02:25:47.406
<i>I remind you that you're</i>
<i>still under subpoena.</i>
<i>Mr. Corleone.</i>

1447
02:25:47.441 --> 02:25:49.210
<i>This court is adjourned!</i>

1448
02:25:49.245 --> 02:25:52.983
(PEOPLE CHATTERING
ANIMATEDLY)

1449
02:25:53.018 --> 02:25:55.579
Ten-to-one (CHUCKLES)
ten-to-one shot. you said.

1450
02:25:55.614 --> 02:25:59.550
A ten-to-one shot
he would take the Fifth.
and I'd lose.

1451
02:26:00.927 --> 02:26:02.553
You sound
like my bookie.

1452
02:26:02.588 --> 02:26:04.423
I owe that monkey
my life.

1453
02:26:06.493 --> 02:26:08.295
Well. just get
a good night's sleep.

1454
02:26:08.330 --> 02:26:10.033
(GRUMBLING)
Yeah. Good night.

1455
02:26:10.068 --> 02:26:12.266
You've got
a big day
tomorrow.

1456
02:26:12.301 --> 02:26:15.335
I've got you
a new suit. new
shirt. new tie.

1457
02:26:16.976 --> 02:26:20.109
I'm gonna shave you myself
in the morning.

1458
02:26:20.144 --> 02:26:24.245
And you're gonna look
respectable for 50 million
of your fellow Americans.

1459
02:26:24.280 --> 02:26:28.348
Tomorrow... My life?
My life won't be worth
a nickel after tomorrow.

1460
02:26:30.649 --> 02:26:33.518
Come on! I saw this...
I saw this 19 times.

1461
02:26:35.357 --> 02:26:37.863
FBI MAN 1: You've got
a great home here. Frankie.

1462
02:26:37.898 --> 02:26:39.326
for the rest of your life.

1463
02:26:39.361 --> 02:26:41.130
Nobody gets near you.
you're not going anywhere.

1464
02:26:41.165 --> 02:26:42.461
(BILLIARD BALLS CLATTERING)

1465
02:26:42.496 --> 02:26:44.199
That's great. Beautiful.

1466
02:26:45.301 --> 02:26:47.334
Some deal I made.

1467
02:26:47.369 --> 02:26:50.238
Ah. you'll live like a king.
You'll be a hero.

1468
02:26:50.273 --> 02:26:53.142
You'll live better here than
most people on the outside.

1469
02:26:53.177 --> 02:26:54.572
Some deal!

1470
02:26:54.607 --> 02:26:56.310
(SCOFFS)

1471
02:26:58.248 --> 02:26:59.643
MICHAEL:
(WHISPERING)
Alive.

1472
02:26:59.678 --> 02:27:01.953
Pentangeli
is alive.

1473
02:27:03.616 --> 02:27:05.924
How did they get
their hands on him?

1474
02:27:05.959 --> 02:27:07.618
Roth.

1475
02:27:07.653 --> 02:27:10.159
He engineered it.
Michael.

1476
02:27:10.194 --> 02:27:12.590
When Frankie went
to make a deal with
the Rosato brothers

1477
02:27:12.625 --> 02:27:14.526
and they tried to kill him.

1478
02:27:14.561 --> 02:27:18.134
He thought you
double-crossed him.

1479
02:27:18.169 --> 02:27:21.203
Our people with the
New York detectives said
he was half dead. scared stiff

1480
02:27:21.238 --> 02:27:24.470
and talking out loud
that you'd turned on him.

1481
02:27:24.505 --> 02:27:28.881
They already had him
on possession. bookmaking.
murder one and a lot more.

1482
02:27:30.412 --> 02:27:33.215
The FBI has him
airtight.

1483
02:27:33.250 --> 02:27:36.251
He's on an army base.
24 hour guards.

1484
02:27:36.286 --> 02:27:38.451
TOM: No way we can get to him.

1485
02:27:38.486 --> 02:27:40.651
We've opened it up
to five counts of perjury.

1486
02:27:43.425 --> 02:27:46.591
What about Fredo?
What does he know?

1487
02:27:46.626 --> 02:27:50.364
He says he doesn't
know anything.
and I believe him.

1488
02:27:50.399 --> 02:27:54.302
Roth. well. he...he played
this one beautifully.

1489
02:28:02.312 --> 02:28:04.081
I'm going to
talk to Fredo.

1490
02:28:44.156 --> 02:28:45.991
I haven't got
a lot to say. Mike.

1491
02:28:48.490 --> 02:28:49.962
We have time.

1492
02:28:51.427 --> 02:28:53.625
I was kept
pretty much
in the dark.

1493
02:28:55.695 --> 02:28:57.398
I didn't know
all that much.

1494
02:28:58.797 --> 02:29:01.633
What about now?

1495
02:29:01.668 --> 02:29:04.273
Is there anything
you can help me out with?

1496
02:29:04.308 --> 02:29:06.539
Anything you can
tell me now?

1497
02:29:08.444 --> 02:29:10.642
They've got Pentangeli.
That's all I can tell you.

1498
02:29:25.692 --> 02:29:29.364
I didn't know
it was going to be
a hit. Mike.

1499
02:29:29.399 --> 02:29:31.630
I swear to God I didn't know
it was gonna be a hit.

1500
02:29:34.668 --> 02:29:38.406
Johnny Ola
bumped into me
in Beverly Hills.

1501
02:29:40.806 --> 02:29:43.048
He said that he
wanted to talk.

1502
02:29:45.547 --> 02:29:48.449
He said that
you and...and Roth

1503
02:29:48.484 --> 02:29:51.518
were in on a
big deal together.

1504
02:29:54.325 --> 02:29:58.459
And that there was
something in it for me
if I could help him out.

1505
02:29:58.494 --> 02:30:02.430
He said that you
were being tough
on the negotiations

1506
02:30:02.465 --> 02:30:04.696
but if they could get
a little help

1507
02:30:04.731 --> 02:30:06.665
and close
the deal fast.

1508
02:30:08.603 --> 02:30:11.241
it...it would be good
for the family.

1509
02:30:12.640 --> 02:30:15.410
And you believed
that story?

1510
02:30:15.445 --> 02:30:17.346
You believed that?

1511
02:30:17.381 --> 02:30:19.744
He said there was
something in it for me.

1512
02:30:19.779 --> 02:30:21.482
on my own!

1513
02:30:21.517 --> 02:30:23.616
I've always taken
care of you. Fredo.

1514
02:30:23.651 --> 02:30:25.321
(INCREDULOUSLY)
Taken care of me?

1515
02:30:26.786 --> 02:30:30.557
You're my kid brother!
You take care of me?

1516
02:30:30.592 --> 02:30:32.328
Did you ever think
about that. huh?

1517
02:30:32.363 --> 02:30:35.793
Did you ever once
think about that?

1518
02:30:35.828 --> 02:30:40.567
"Send Fredo off to do this.
send Fredo off to do that!"

1519
02:30:40.602 --> 02:30:45.242
"Let Fredo take care
of some Mickey Mouse
nightclub somewhere."

1520
02:30:45.277 --> 02:30:48.113
"Send Fredo to pick
somebody at the airport!"

1521
02:30:48.148 --> 02:30:50.577
I'm your older brother.
but was stepped over!

1522
02:30:50.612 --> 02:30:52.645
MICHAEL: (SOFTLY)
That's the way Pop wanted it.

1523
02:30:52.680 --> 02:30:54.515
It ain't the way
I wanted it!

1524
02:30:56.420 --> 02:30:58.882
I can handle things.
I'm smart!

1525
02:30:58.917 --> 02:31:01.225
Not like everybody says.

1526
02:31:01.260 --> 02:31:04.261
Like dumb. I'm smart
and I want respect!

1527
02:31:12.898 --> 02:31:16.669
Is there
anything you can tell me
about this investigation?

1528
02:31:16.704 --> 02:31:18.275
Anything more?

1529
02:31:26.285 --> 02:31:28.549
The Senate lawyer.
Questadt.

1530
02:31:30.454 --> 02:31:31.882
He belongs to Roth.

1531
02:31:39.694 --> 02:31:41.793
(SIGHS)

1532
02:31:41.828 --> 02:31:43.300
Fredo.

1533
02:31:45.898 --> 02:31:47.667
you're nothing
to me now.

1534
02:31:50.573 --> 02:31:51.902
You're not a brother.

1535
02:31:51.937 --> 02:31:53.277
not a friend.

1536
02:31:54.709 --> 02:31:56.742
I don't want to know you.
or what you do.

1537
02:31:58.878 --> 02:32:00.680
I don't want to see you
at the hotels.

1538
02:32:01.980 --> 02:32:03.782
I don't want you
near my house.

1539
02:32:06.556 --> 02:32:08.391
When you see
our mother.

1540
02:32:08.426 --> 02:32:10.723
I want to know a day
in advance.
so I won't be there.

1541
02:32:12.793 --> 02:32:14.529
You understand?

1542
02:32:24.343 --> 02:32:25.606
Mikey.

1543
02:32:32.747 --> 02:32:36.650
I don't want
anything to happen to him
while my mother's alive.

1544
02:33:13.557 --> 02:33:16.591
(PEOPLE CHATTERING SOFTLY)

1545
02:33:18.859 --> 02:33:20.793
REPORTER: Here he comes now.

1546
02:33:26.471 --> 02:33:28.537
There's more people
than at a ballgame in here.

1547
02:33:28.572 --> 02:33:29.967
(LAUGHING)

1548
02:33:30.002 --> 02:33:32.002
Hey. there's
Willi Cicci!

1549
02:33:32.037 --> 02:33:33.608
MAN: Frankie Five-Angels...

1550
02:33:53.630 --> 02:33:56.301
CHAIRMAN:<i> This committee</i>
<i>will come to order!</i>

1551
02:33:58.899 --> 02:34:00.404
<i>State your name.</i>
<i>please.</i>

1552
02:34:00.439 --> 02:34:01.801
PENTANGELI:<i> Frank Pentangeli.</i>

1553
02:34:01.836 --> 02:34:03.506
CHAIRMAN:<i> And where</i>
<i>were you born?</i>

1554
02:34:03.541 --> 02:34:05.772
PENTANGELI:<i> Partinico.</i>
<i>it's outside of Palermo.</i>

1555
02:34:05.807 --> 02:34:07.873
<i>And where do you</i>
<i>live now?</i>

1556
02:34:07.908 --> 02:34:12.317
<i>I live in an army barracks</i>
<i>with the FBI guys.</i>

1557
02:34:12.352 --> 02:34:14.352
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

1558
02:34:14.387 --> 02:34:18.851
<i>We have here. finally.</i>
<i>a witness that will</i>
<i>further testify</i>

1559
02:34:18.886 --> 02:34:21.722
<i>to Michael Corleone's rule</i>
<i>of a criminal empire</i>

1560
02:34:21.757 --> 02:34:25.660
<i>that controls all gambling</i>
<i>in this country...and perhaps</i>
<i>another country.</i>

1561
02:34:25.695 --> 02:34:27.728
<i>This witness</i>
<i>has had no buffer</i>

1562
02:34:27.763 --> 02:34:30.599
<i>between himself</i>
<i>and Michael Corleone.</i>

1563
02:34:30.634 --> 02:34:33.734
<i>He can corroborate</i>
<i>our charges on enough counts</i>

1564
02:34:33.769 --> 02:34:38.607
<i>for us to recommend</i>
<i>a charge of perjury</i>
<i>against Michael Corleone.</i>

1565
02:34:38.642 --> 02:34:40.642
Senator.
Thank you. Chairman.

1566
02:34:41.777 --> 02:34:43.480
SENATOR:
<i>Mr. Pentangeli.</i>

1567
02:34:44.879 --> 02:34:47.451
<i>Mr. Pentangeli.</i>

1568
02:34:47.486 --> 02:34:50.718
<i>Were you a member</i>
<i>of the Corleone family?</i>

1569
02:34:50.753 --> 02:34:55.756
<i>Did you serve</i>
<i>under Caporegime.</i>
<i>Peter Clemenza.</i>

1570
02:34:55.791 --> 02:34:59.892
<i>and under Vito Corleone.</i>
<i>also known as the Godfather?</i>

1571
02:35:06.032 --> 02:35:09.000
<i>I. uh. I never knew</i>
<i>any Godfather.</i>

1572
02:35:09.035 --> 02:35:11.101
(PEOPLE MURMURING)

1573
02:35:11.136 --> 02:35:13.510
<i>I have</i>
<i>my own family. Senator.</i>

1574
02:35:16.779 --> 02:35:19.516
QUESTADT:
<i>Mr. Pentangeli. you. uh...</i>

1575
02:35:19.551 --> 02:35:21.749
<i>You are contradicting</i>
<i>your own sworn statement</i>

1576
02:35:21.784 --> 02:35:23.916
<i>that you previously</i>
<i>made to me and signed.</i>

1577
02:35:23.951 --> 02:35:27.557
<i>I ask you again. sir.</i>
<i>here and now under oath...</i>

1578
02:35:27.592 --> 02:35:31.825
<i>were you at any time</i>
<i>a member of</i>
<i>a crime organization</i>

1579
02:35:31.860 --> 02:35:33.827
<i>led by Michael Corleone?</i>

1580
02:35:33.862 --> 02:35:35.565
<i>I don't know</i>
<i>nothing about that!</i>

1581
02:35:36.964 --> 02:35:39.965
<i>Oh!</i>

1582
02:35:40.000 --> 02:35:44.002
<i>I was in</i>
<i>the olive oil business</i>
<i>with his father</i>

1583
02:35:44.037 --> 02:35:47.709
<i>but that was</i>
<i>a long time ago.</i>
<i>That's all.</i>

1584
02:35:47.744 --> 02:35:50.877
<i>We have a sworn affidavit.</i>

1585
02:35:50.912 --> 02:35:52.516
<i>We have it.</i>

1586
02:35:52.551 --> 02:35:54.914
<i>Your sworn affidavit.</i>
<i>that you murdered</i>

1587
02:35:54.949 --> 02:35:56.916
<i>on the orders of</i>
<i>Michael Corleone.</i>

1588
02:35:56.951 --> 02:35:58.918
<i>Do you deny</i>
<i>this confession.</i>

1589
02:35:58.953 --> 02:36:01.954
<i>and do you realize</i>
<i>what will happen as a result</i>
<i>of your denial?</i>

1590
02:36:01.989 --> 02:36:05.155
<i>Look. the FBI guys.</i>
<i>they promised me a deal</i>

1591
02:36:05.190 --> 02:36:08.895
<i>so I made up a lot of stuff</i>
<i>about Michael Corleone.</i>

1592
02:36:08.930 --> 02:36:11.161
<i>'cause that's what</i>
<i>they wanted.</i>

1593
02:36:11.196 --> 02:36:13.603
(STUTTERS)
<i>But it was all lies.</i>

1594
02:36:13.638 --> 02:36:15.902
<i>Uh... Everything!</i>

1595
02:36:15.937 --> 02:36:18.102
<i>They kept saying. uh.</i>

1596
02:36:18.137 --> 02:36:22.975
<i>"Michael Corleone did this"</i>
<i>and "Michael Corleone</i>
<i>did that".</i>

1597
02:36:24.781 --> 02:36:28.882
<i>So I said. uh.</i>
<i>"Yeah. sure.</i>
<i>Why not?"</i>

1598
02:36:28.917 --> 02:36:30.851
<i>Mr. Corleone. would you</i>

1599
02:36:30.886 --> 02:36:34.954
<i>kindly identify the gentleman</i>
<i>sitting to your left?</i>

1600
02:36:34.989 --> 02:36:36.186
I can
answer that.

1601
02:36:37.662 --> 02:36:40.828
His name is
Vincenzo Pentangeli.

1602
02:36:40.863 --> 02:36:43.468
SENATOR 2:<i> Is he related</i>
<i>to the witness?</i>

1603
02:36:43.503 --> 02:36:45.701
He is. I believe.
his brother.

1604
02:36:45.736 --> 02:36:48.099
<i>Will he come forward</i>
<i>and be sworn. sir?</i>

1605
02:36:48.134 --> 02:36:50.541
Sir. this man doesn't
understand English.

1606
02:36:50.576 --> 02:36:54.006
He came at his own expense
to aid his brother
in this time of trouble.

1607
02:36:54.041 --> 02:36:55.678
He's not under subpoena

1608
02:36:55.713 --> 02:36:57.779
and his reputation in his
own country is impeccable.

1609
02:36:57.814 --> 02:36:59.781
QUESTADT:
<i>Are you saying he knows</i>
<i>nothing about these matters?</i>

1610
02:36:59.816 --> 02:37:01.915
To my knowledge.
nothing.

1611
02:37:01.950 --> 02:37:04.654
<i>I'm going to find out</i>
<i>what happened!</i>

1612
02:37:04.689 --> 02:37:06.656
<i>All right. this committee</i>
<i>is now adjourned.</i>

1613
02:37:06.691 --> 02:37:08.086
<i>The witness is excused.</i>

1614
02:37:08.121 --> 02:37:10.121
TOM: Senator!

1615
02:37:10.156 --> 02:37:14.158
Senator! This committee
owes an apology!

1616
02:37:14.193 --> 02:37:18.195
This committee
owes an apology.
Apology. Senator!

1617
02:37:26.810 --> 02:37:30.515
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

1618
02:37:45.796 --> 02:37:48.027
Michael. excuse me.

1619
02:37:48.062 --> 02:37:50.227
Hello. darling.

1620
02:37:50.262 --> 02:37:52.196
The children are outside.
We're going.

1621
02:37:55.102 --> 02:37:57.135
What do you mean going?
We're all gonna
leave tomorrow.

1622
02:37:58.710 --> 02:38:00.204
Uh. Rocco?

1623
02:38:02.076 --> 02:38:03.680
I'll be in
my room. Mike.

1624
02:38:07.246 --> 02:38:10.313
Michael. I'm not
going back to Nevada.

1625
02:38:10.348 --> 02:38:12.887
I brought the children
to say goodbye to you.

1626
02:38:17.124 --> 02:38:19.564
I want you to know.
I'm very happy for you.

1627
02:38:19.599 --> 02:38:24.030
I suppose I always knew
you were too smart
to let any of them beat you.

1628
02:38:25.704 --> 02:38:26.934
Why don't you
sit down?

1629
02:38:26.969 --> 02:38:30.333
No. no. I'm not going
to stay long.

1630
02:38:30.368 --> 02:38:34.579
There are some things
I'd like to talk to you about.

1631
02:38:34.614 --> 02:38:36.845
Some things that have
been on my mind.

1632
02:38:38.112 --> 02:38:39.683
changes
I want to make.

1633
02:38:39.718 --> 02:38:41.883
I think it's too late
for changes. Michael.

1634
02:38:43.953 --> 02:38:46.250
I promised myself.
I wasn't going to
say anything and now...

1635
02:38:46.285 --> 02:38:48.758
MICHAEL: What do you mean.
"too late"?

1636
02:38:53.930 --> 02:38:56.568
What really happened
with Pentangeli. Michael?

1637
02:39:02.642 --> 02:39:04.873
His brother came
and helped him.

1638
02:39:04.908 --> 02:39:06.710
KAY: I didn't even know
he had a brother.

1639
02:39:07.944 --> 02:39:09.779
And where is he now?

1640
02:39:11.046 --> 02:39:13.013
He's on a plane.
back to Sicily.

1641
02:39:14.313 --> 02:39:16.247
All he had to do
was show his face.

1642
02:39:18.691 --> 02:39:21.252
It was between
the brothers. Kay.

1643
02:39:21.287 --> 02:39:22.891
I had nothing
to do with it.

1644
02:39:30.197 --> 02:39:32.164
(GIGGLING)

1645
02:39:32.199 --> 02:39:36.168
MICHAEL:
I don't want you going!
Not you. not the kids. No.

1646
02:39:36.203 --> 02:39:38.236
You're my wife.
they're my children.

1647
02:39:38.271 --> 02:39:40.975
I love you and
won't allow it.

1648
02:39:41.010 --> 02:39:42.680
Michael. you say you love me.

1649
02:39:42.715 --> 02:39:45.078
and then you talk about
allowing me to leave!

1650
02:39:45.113 --> 02:39:47.179
Listen. there are things that
have been going on for years

1651
02:39:47.214 --> 02:39:49.412
between men and women
that will not change.
Michael. you're blind.

1652
02:39:49.447 --> 02:39:51.150
You've become blind.
Michael!
Blind to what?

1653
02:39:51.185 --> 02:39:53.658
Look what's happened to us.

1654
02:39:53.693 --> 02:39:56.727
My. God! Look what's happened
to our son. Michael!
Nothing's happened to him.

1655
02:39:56.762 --> 02:39:58.729
Don't tell me nothing's...
MICHAEL: Anthony's fine!

1656
02:39:58.764 --> 02:40:00.962
Anthony is not fine!
I don't want to
hear about it.

1657
02:40:00.997 --> 02:40:03.294
You will hear about it.
Anthony's friends...
I don't want to hear about it.

1658
02:40:03.329 --> 02:40:05.769
MICHAEL: I don't want to
hear about it!
...are your button men!

1659
02:40:07.267 --> 02:40:08.772
Over!

1660
02:40:21.446 --> 02:40:24.348
At this moment
I feel no love
for you at all.

1661
02:40:26.220 --> 02:40:28.286
I never thought
that would ever happen.

1662
02:40:29.894 --> 02:40:31.421
but it has.

1663
02:40:45.140 --> 02:40:46.744
Kay...

1664
02:40:50.442 --> 02:40:53.344
We're leaving
tomorrow.

1665
02:40:53.379 --> 02:40:56.721
Kay. why don't you
take the kids
back to their room?

1666
02:40:56.756 --> 02:40:58.789
Michael.
you haven't heard me.

1667
02:40:58.824 --> 02:41:01.726
Kay. what do you
want from me?

1668
02:41:02.828 --> 02:41:05.059
Do you expect me
to let you go?

1669
02:41:05.094 --> 02:41:09.932
Do you expect me to let you
take my children from me?

1670
02:41:09.967 --> 02:41:13.232
Don't you know me?
Don't you know that
that's an impossibility?

1671
02:41:13.267 --> 02:41:15.465
That. that could never happen.

1672
02:41:15.500 --> 02:41:20.107
That I'd use all my power
to keep something like that
from happening?

1673
02:41:20.142 --> 02:41:21.944
Don't you know that?

1674
02:41:24.344 --> 02:41:26.278
Kay...

1675
02:41:29.151 --> 02:41:30.854
In time.

1676
02:41:32.154 --> 02:41:33.318
you'll feel
differently.

1677
02:41:35.289 --> 02:41:37.223
You'll be glad
I stopped you now.

1678
02:41:40.195 --> 02:41:41.359
I know that.

1679
02:41:44.166 --> 02:41:46.837
I know you blame me
for losing the baby.

1680
02:41:49.435 --> 02:41:51.842
Yes.

1681
02:41:51.877 --> 02:41:53.437
I know what that
meant to you.

1682
02:41:56.508 --> 02:41:59.443
I'll make it up
to you. Kay.

1683
02:41:59.478 --> 02:42:02.413
I swear
I'll make it up
to you. I'll...

1684
02:42:03.856 --> 02:42:07.088
I'm going to change.

1685
02:42:07.123 --> 02:42:11.290
I'll change.
I've learned that I have
the strength to change.

1686
02:42:13.393 --> 02:42:15.492
Then you'll forget
about this miscarriage

1687
02:42:17.298 --> 02:42:19.298
and we'll have
another child.

1688
02:42:19.333 --> 02:42:22.202
And we'll go on.
you and I.

1689
02:42:23.436 --> 02:42:24.501
We'll go on.

1690
02:42:24.536 --> 02:42:26.206
(GROANS)

1691
02:42:26.241 --> 02:42:27.812
Oh. Michael!

1692
02:42:28.881 --> 02:42:30.848
Michael. you are blind.

1693
02:42:32.577 --> 02:42:35.083
It wasn't
a miscarriage.

1694
02:42:37.318 --> 02:42:38.515
It was an abortion.

1695
02:42:40.893 --> 02:42:43.388
An abortion.
Michael.

1696
02:42:43.423 --> 02:42:46.930
Just like our marriage
is an abortion.

1697
02:42:46.965 --> 02:42:49.966
Something that's
unholy and evil!

1698
02:42:51.871 --> 02:42:55.070
I didn't want
your son. Michael!

1699
02:42:55.105 --> 02:42:58.975
I wouldn't bring
another one of your sons
into this world!

1700
02:43:00.979 --> 02:43:03.408
It was an abortion.
Michael.

1701
02:43:03.443 --> 02:43:05.245
It was a son

1702
02:43:05.280 --> 02:43:10.580
and I had it killed
because this must all end!

1703
02:43:10.615 --> 02:43:13.187
I know now
that it's over.

1704
02:43:13.222 --> 02:43:14.826
I knew it then.

1705
02:43:16.060 --> 02:43:18.456
There would be
no way. Michael.

1706
02:43:18.491 --> 02:43:21.558
no way you could
ever forgive me.

1707
02:43:21.593 --> 02:43:26.332
Not with this Sicilian thing
that's been going on
for 2.000...

1708
02:43:26.367 --> 02:43:28.004
(SCREAMS)

1709
02:43:30.305 --> 02:43:33.009
(SEETHING)

1710
02:43:34.243 --> 02:43:36.144
You won't take
my children.

1711
02:43:36.179 --> 02:43:37.475
(SOBBING) I will.

1712
02:43:37.510 --> 02:43:39.180
(BELLOWING) You won't
take my children!

1713
02:43:39.215 --> 02:43:41.314
(SOBBING) They're
my children too.

1714
02:43:46.057 --> 02:43:49.927
(BAND PLAYING)

1715
02:44:55.522 --> 02:45:00.162
(ALL CHATTERING)

1716
02:45:08.238 --> 02:45:11.371
Fredo. give this
to Grandmother.

1717
02:45:13.078 --> 02:45:16.673
(ALL COMMENTING APPRECIATIVELY
IN ITALIAN)

1718
02:45:44.769 --> 02:45:49.277
(CHATTERING IN ITALIAN)

1719
02:46:04.723 --> 02:46:05.755
(CHUCKLING)

1720
02:46:12.137 --> 02:46:15.600
(TOASTING IN ITALIAN)

1721
02:47:20.139 --> 02:47:23.371
(ROUSING QUIETLY)

1722
02:47:26.541 --> 02:47:28.772
(IN ITALIAN)

1723
02:47:48.629 --> 02:47:51.135
(READING IN ENGLISH)

1724
02:48:25.369 --> 02:48:28.304
(BECKONS IN ITALIAN)

1725
02:48:43.717 --> 02:48:45.486
(STATES HIS NAME
IN ITALIAN)

1726
02:48:45.521 --> 02:48:46.685
(REPEATS
INQUISITIVELY)

1727
02:48:46.720 --> 02:48:47.752
(LAUGHS)

1728
02:49:12.416 --> 02:49:13.646
(SCREAMING)

1729
02:49:13.681 --> 02:49:16.550
(CURSING IN ITALIAN)

1730
02:49:19.324 --> 02:49:20.587
(GUN FIRING)

1731
02:49:20.622 --> 02:49:22.358
(CAR ENGINE STARTING)

1732
02:49:27.827 --> 02:49:29.629
(WARNING)

1733
02:49:32.601 --> 02:49:34.370
(GROANING)

1734
02:50:33.057 --> 02:50:35.794
Michael. say goodbye.

1735
02:51:38.925 --> 02:51:40.496
Hi. Al.

1736
02:51:51.641 --> 02:51:55.038
Tom? Can I speak with you
for a second. Tom?

1737
02:52:03.488 --> 02:52:05.081
Tom. where's Mike?

1738
02:52:06.458 --> 02:52:07.787
Waiting for you
to leave.

1739
02:52:10.990 --> 02:52:12.957
Can I talk
with him?

1740
02:52:12.992 --> 02:52:14.728
Sorry. Fredo.
No chance.

1741
02:52:16.061 --> 02:52:17.434
CONNIE:
Can I see him?

1742
02:52:17.469 --> 02:52:18.798
He's in
the boathouse.

1743
02:52:32.583 --> 02:52:34.946
CONNIE: Michael.
it's Connie.

1744
02:52:56.134 --> 02:52:57.804
Michael...

1745
02:53:00.809 --> 02:53:04.041
I'd like to stay
close to home now.
if it's all right.

1746
02:53:12.821 --> 02:53:14.183
Is Kay coming?

1747
02:53:17.595 --> 02:53:18.726
No.

1748
02:53:26.835 --> 02:53:30.133
Fredo's in the house
with Mama.

1749
02:53:30.168 --> 02:53:34.137
He asked for you
and Tom said
you wouldn't see him.

1750
02:53:37.714 --> 02:53:38.812
That's right.

1751
02:53:42.620 --> 02:53:45.885
Kids. why don't you
go outside for a while?

1752
02:53:49.528 --> 02:53:51.187
Please. I want to
talk to you.

1753
02:54:03.069 --> 02:54:07.775
Michael. I hated you
for so many years.

1754
02:54:07.810 --> 02:54:10.580
I think I did
things to myself.

1755
02:54:10.615 --> 02:54:13.110
to hurt myself.
so that you'd know

1756
02:54:16.280 --> 02:54:18.588
that I could
hurt you.

1757
02:54:24.629 --> 02:54:29.599
You were just being
strong for all of us.
the way Papa was.

1758
02:54:29.634 --> 02:54:31.535
And I forgive you.

1759
02:54:36.036 --> 02:54:39.037
Can't you forgive
Fredo?

1760
02:54:39.072 --> 02:54:42.876
He's so sweet.
and helpless without you.

1761
02:54:50.050 --> 02:54:51.654
You need me. Michael.

1762
02:54:51.689 --> 02:54:53.216
I want to take care
of you now.

1763
02:55:03.833 --> 02:55:05.228
Connie.

1764
02:56:47.431 --> 02:56:49.233
Tom. sit down.

1765
02:56:54.911 --> 02:56:58.341
(INQUIRING
IN ITALIAN)

1766
02:57:01.951 --> 02:57:05.722
Our friend
and business partner.
Hyman Roth. is in the news.

1767
02:57:07.022 --> 02:57:09.022
Did you hear
about it?

1768
02:57:09.057 --> 02:57:10.386
I hear that he's
in Israel.

1769
02:57:10.421 --> 02:57:12.894
Mmm-hmm.

1770
02:57:12.929 --> 02:57:16.931
The High Court in Israel
turned down his request
to live there as a return Jew.

1771
02:57:16.966 --> 02:57:18.328
His passport's
been invalidated.

1772
02:57:18.363 --> 02:57:20.462
except for return
to the United States.

1773
02:57:20.497 --> 02:57:23.773
He landed in Buenos Aires
yesterday.

1774
02:57:23.808 --> 02:57:26.710
He offered a gift
of a million dollars
if they'd let him live there.

1775
02:57:28.472 --> 02:57:30.472
They turned him down.

1776
02:57:30.507 --> 02:57:32.749
He's going
to try Panama.

1777
02:57:32.784 --> 02:57:34.850
Panama
won't take him.

1778
02:57:34.885 --> 02:57:37.787
Not for a million.
not for ten million.

1779
02:57:37.822 --> 02:57:39.921
ROCCO: His condition is
reported as terminal.

1780
02:57:39.956 --> 02:57:42.154
He's only gonna live
another six months anyway.

1781
02:57:42.189 --> 02:57:44.695
He's been dying of the same
heart attack for 20 years.

1782
02:57:45.830 --> 02:57:47.423
That plane
goes to Miami.

1783
02:57:47.458 --> 02:57:49.997
MICHAEL: That's right.
That's where I want it met.

1784
02:57:51.099 --> 02:57:53.000
Mike. that's impossible.

1785
02:57:53.035 --> 02:57:54.771
They'll turn him over
directly to
the Internal Revenue.

1786
02:57:54.806 --> 02:57:56.465
Customs and half the FBI.

1787
02:57:56.500 --> 02:57:58.368
It's not impossible.

1788
02:57:58.403 --> 02:58:00.139
Nothing's impossible.

1789
02:58:00.174 --> 02:58:01.877
It would be
like trying to kill
the President.

1790
02:58:01.912 --> 02:58:03.406
There's no way
we can get to him!

1791
02:58:03.441 --> 02:58:04.979
Tom. you know.
you surprise me.

1792
02:58:08.886 --> 02:58:10.754
If anything in this life
is certain.

1793
02:58:12.384 --> 02:58:14.120
if history has
taught us anything.

1794
02:58:15.860 --> 02:58:17.420
it's that you
can kill anyone.

1795
02:58:23.802 --> 02:58:25.461
Rocco?

1796
02:58:25.496 --> 02:58:29.003
Difficult.
Not impossible.

1797
02:58:29.038 --> 02:58:30.807
Good.

1798
02:58:33.174 --> 02:58:35.779
Why did you ask me
if something was wrong
when I came in?

1799
02:58:40.412 --> 02:58:42.753
MICHAEL: I thought you were
going to tell me that

1800
02:58:44.185 --> 02:58:47.791
you were moving
your family to Vegas

1801
02:58:47.826 --> 02:58:51.520
and that you'd been offered
the. uh. Vice Presidency of
the Houstan hotels there.

1802
02:58:53.326 --> 02:58:54.996
I thought that you were
gonna tell me that.

1803
02:58:55.031 --> 02:58:57.064
I turned 'em down

1804
02:58:57.099 --> 02:59:00.034
I mean do I have
to tell you about every
offer that I turn down?

1805
02:59:02.500 --> 02:59:04.203
Let's do business.

1806
02:59:04.238 --> 02:59:05.501
TOM: All right.

1807
02:59:07.406 --> 02:59:09.846
Just consider this. Michael.
That's all. Just consider it.

1808
02:59:11.608 --> 02:59:13.916
Now. Roth and the Rosatos
are on the run.

1809
02:59:13.951 --> 02:59:16.952
Are they worth it.
are they strong enough?

1810
02:59:16.987 --> 02:59:19.218
Is it worth it?

1811
02:59:19.253 --> 02:59:21.957
You've won. Do you want
to wipe everybody out?

1812
02:59:21.992 --> 02:59:25.224
I don't feel I have to
wipe everybody out. Tom.

1813
02:59:25.259 --> 02:59:27.259
Just my enemies.
that's all.

1814
02:59:34.939 --> 02:59:37.500
Are you gonna come along
with me on these things
I have to do. or what?

1815
02:59:39.944 --> 02:59:45.310
Because if not.
you can take your wife.
your family and your mistress

1816
02:59:45.345 --> 02:59:47.147
and move them all
to Las Vegas.

1817
02:59:48.645 --> 02:59:50.216
(SNORTS)

1818
02:59:51.516 --> 02:59:53.351
Why do you hurt me.
Michael?

1819
02:59:53.386 --> 02:59:55.419
I've always been
loyal to you.
I mean...

1820
02:59:55.454 --> 02:59:56.860
What is this?

1821
03:00:01.163 --> 03:00:02.998
(IN ITALIAN)

1822
03:00:10.007 --> 03:00:12.403
Now. what is it that
you want me to do?

1823
03:00:12.438 --> 03:00:14.636
Hey. Anthony.

1824
03:00:14.671 --> 03:00:16.506
Anthony. how would
you like it if I...

1825
03:00:16.541 --> 03:00:17.914
How would you like it
if I taught you

1826
03:00:17.949 --> 03:00:19.509
how to catch
the really big fish?

1827
03:00:19.544 --> 03:00:20.884
Would you
like that?

1828
03:00:20.919 --> 03:00:22.347
Okay.

1829
03:00:22.382 --> 03:00:25.482
You know.
when I was your age.

1830
03:00:25.517 --> 03:00:32.489
I went out fishing
with all my brothers
and my father. Everybody.

1831
03:00:32.524 --> 03:00:36.097
I was... I was
the only one that
caught a fish.

1832
03:00:37.936 --> 03:00:40.365
Nobody else
could catch one.

1833
03:00:40.400 --> 03:00:43.973
Do you know
how I did it?

1834
03:00:44.008 --> 03:00:47.570
Every time I put
the line in the water
I said a Hail Mary

1835
03:00:47.605 --> 03:00:50.210
and every time
I said a Hail Mary.
I caught a fish.

1836
03:00:53.677 --> 03:00:56.282
Do you believe that?
It's true.

1837
03:00:56.317 --> 03:00:58.020
That's the secret.

1838
03:01:00.057 --> 03:01:01.617
Do you want to try it
out on the lake?

1839
03:01:01.652 --> 03:01:03.355
Okay.
Okay.

1840
03:01:05.557 --> 03:01:06.963
What else
have you got?

1841
03:01:32.254 --> 03:01:34.023
(SIGHS
FORCEFULLY)

1842
03:01:34.058 --> 03:01:36.223
Everything's gonna
be okay. Frankie.
don't worry.

1843
03:01:36.258 --> 03:01:40.227
Did my brother
go back?
Yeah. don't worry.

1844
03:01:40.262 --> 03:01:42.295
He's ten times
tougher than me.
my brother.

1845
03:01:43.463 --> 03:01:46.167
He's old-fashioned.
Yeah.

1846
03:01:46.202 --> 03:01:47.465
He didn't even want
to go out to dinner.

1847
03:01:47.500 --> 03:01:49.566
he just wanted
to go straight home.

1848
03:01:49.601 --> 03:01:51.601
That's my brother!

1849
03:01:51.636 --> 03:01:54.978
There's nothing could
get him away from
that two-mule town.

1850
03:01:55.013 --> 03:01:57.607
He could have been
big here. He could have
had his own family.

1851
03:02:04.055 --> 03:02:05.219
Tom.

1852
03:02:06.552 --> 03:02:08.156
what do I do now?

1853
03:02:09.786 --> 03:02:11.126
Frankie.

1854
03:02:16.430 --> 03:02:19.497
You were always interested
in politics and history.

1855
03:02:22.073 --> 03:02:25.503
I remember you
talking about Hitler
back in '33.

1856
03:02:25.538 --> 03:02:27.076
Yeah. I still
read a lot.

1857
03:02:27.111 --> 03:02:28.638
I get good stuff
in there.

1858
03:02:31.709 --> 03:02:34.347
You were around
the old-timers.

1859
03:02:34.382 --> 03:02:37.548
who dreamed of how
the families should
be organized.

1860
03:02:37.583 --> 03:02:39.286
basing them on
the old Roman legions.

1861
03:02:39.321 --> 03:02:42.619
and call 'em "regimes."
the "capos" and "soldiers".

1862
03:02:44.326 --> 03:02:46.326
And it worked.

1863
03:02:46.361 --> 03:02:49.131
Yeah.
it worked.

1864
03:02:49.166 --> 03:02:51.529
Those were the great
old days. you know.

1865
03:02:52.763 --> 03:02:56.072
We was like
the Roman Empire.

1866
03:02:56.107 --> 03:02:59.042
The Corleone family
was like the Roman Empire.

1867
03:03:01.838 --> 03:03:04.080
Yeah.

1868
03:03:04.115 --> 03:03:05.510
it was once.

1869
03:03:10.715 --> 03:03:12.385
Frankie.

1870
03:03:22.760 --> 03:03:26.333
When a plot against
the Emperor failed

1871
03:03:27.600 --> 03:03:30.139
the plotters were
always given a chance

1872
03:03:33.111 --> 03:03:35.573
to let their families
keep their fortunes.

1873
03:03:35.608 --> 03:03:36.673
Right?

1874
03:03:36.708 --> 03:03:38.840
Yeah. but only
the rich guys. Tom.

1875
03:03:38.875 --> 03:03:41.183
The little guys.
they got knocked off

1876
03:03:41.218 --> 03:03:43.779
and all their estates
went to the Emperors.

1877
03:03:43.814 --> 03:03:47.156
Unless they went home
and they killed themselves.

1878
03:03:47.191 --> 03:03:49.356
then nothing
happened.

1879
03:03:50.458 --> 03:03:52.326
And their families...

1880
03:03:52.361 --> 03:03:54.196
Their families
were taken
care of. Tom.

1881
03:03:56.431 --> 03:04:00.433
That was a good break.
a nice deal.

1882
03:04:00.468 --> 03:04:02.699
Yeah.

1883
03:04:02.734 --> 03:04:05.075
They. uh.
they went home

1884
03:04:06.243 --> 03:04:09.310
and sat
in a hot bath

1885
03:04:09.345 --> 03:04:10.641
opened up
their veins

1886
03:04:11.875 --> 03:04:15.712
and bled
to death.

1887
03:04:15.747 --> 03:04:18.781
And sometimes they
had a little party
before they did it.

1888
03:04:25.229 --> 03:04:27.559
Don't worry about anything.
Frankie Five-Angels.

1889
03:04:29.167 --> 03:04:30.298
Thanks. Tom.

1890
03:04:31.367 --> 03:04:32.399
Thanks.

1891
03:04:50.848 --> 03:04:52.320
See you. Tom.

1892
03:04:52.355 --> 03:04:54.157
TOM:<i> Addio.</i>
<i>Frankie.</i>

1893
03:05:04.895 --> 03:05:07.467
Kay. You have to go.

1894
03:05:09.801 --> 03:05:10.932
So pretty...

1895
03:05:10.967 --> 03:05:12.637
Kay. please hurry.
He's coming.

1896
03:05:21.978 --> 03:05:24.253
Anthony.

1897
03:05:24.288 --> 03:05:25.815
Kiss Mama goodbye.

1898
03:05:28.490 --> 03:05:31.392
Anthony. will you
kiss your mother
goodbye!

1899
03:05:31.427 --> 03:05:33.922
Anthony.
say goodbye
to Mama.

1900
03:05:33.957 --> 03:05:36.529
Anthony.
I love you.
Anthony.

1901
03:05:37.631 --> 03:05:38.861
Kay. please.

1902
03:05:42.834 --> 03:05:44.339
All right.

1903
03:05:58.256 --> 03:06:00.190
Mary. come here.

1904
03:06:07.694 --> 03:06:09.364
Anthony.

1905
03:06:09.399 --> 03:06:11.465
Anthony. please.
Kiss me once.

1906
03:06:49.769 --> 03:06:51.274
(KAY SOBBING)

1907
03:07:17.665 --> 03:07:20.028
(BOAT ENGINE
ROARING DISTANTLY)

1908
03:07:51.600 --> 03:07:53.666
Easy.

1909
03:07:59.410 --> 03:08:02.543
CONNIE: Anthony!
Anthony!

1910
03:08:02.578 --> 03:08:04.347
He's here.
we're going fishing.

1911
03:08:04.382 --> 03:08:05.645
No!

1912
03:08:05.680 --> 03:08:07.944
Michael wants to
take him to Reno now.

1913
03:08:09.046 --> 03:08:10.617
Oh. shit!

1914
03:08:12.456 --> 03:08:14.819
Okay. kid. you have to
go to Reno with your pop.

1915
03:08:16.922 --> 03:08:18.955
Come on. Anthony.
I'll take you fishing
again tomorrow. okay?

1916
03:08:18.990 --> 03:08:20.330
Huh?
Okay.

1917
03:08:22.796 --> 03:08:24.433
Atta boy.

1918
03:08:24.468 --> 03:08:25.929
Hey. Anthony.

1919
03:08:25.964 --> 03:08:29.834
Listen. I'll catch one
for you in secret. Huh?

1920
03:08:29.869 --> 03:08:31.869
All right. okay. good.

1921
03:08:33.675 --> 03:08:34.740
Okay. let's go.

1922
03:09:14.947 --> 03:09:17.552
Mr. Roth. you understand
I'll have to
take you into custody.

1923
03:09:17.587 --> 03:09:19.180
Yes. I understand.

1924
03:09:19.215 --> 03:09:20.687
REPORTER: Can you give us
your reaction

1925
03:09:20.722 --> 03:09:22.656
to the High Court
of Israel's ruling?

1926
03:09:22.691 --> 03:09:25.560
I'm a retired investor
on a pension.

1927
03:09:25.595 --> 03:09:29.025
I went to Israel because
I wish to live there as a Jew.

1928
03:09:29.060 --> 03:09:30.433
in the twilight of my life.

1929
03:09:36.804 --> 03:09:39.706
Hey. Frankie!
Come on out. let's
play some Hearts.

1930
03:09:48.618 --> 03:09:49.815
Frankie!

1931
03:10:05.866 --> 03:10:09.098
REPORTER 2: Is it true
you're worth over 300
million dollars. Mr. Roth?

1932
03:10:09.133 --> 03:10:12.937
I'm a retired investor.
living on a pension.

1933
03:10:12.972 --> 03:10:16.743
I came home to vote
in the presidential election

1934
03:10:16.778 --> 03:10:19.075
because they
wouldn't give me
an absentee ballot.

1935
03:10:19.110 --> 03:10:20.912
(ALL LAUGHING)

1936
03:10:20.947 --> 03:10:22.012
(GUN FIRING)

1937
03:10:22.047 --> 03:10:23.585
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1938
03:10:25.083 --> 03:10:26.687
(GUN FIRES)

1939
03:10:32.596 --> 03:10:34.024
Jesus Christ.

1940
03:10:35.995 --> 03:10:40.668
FREDO: Hail Mary.
full of grace.
The Lord is with thee.

1941
03:10:42.034 --> 03:10:44.001
Blessed art thou
amongst women.

1942
03:10:45.543 --> 03:10:47.774
Blessed is the fruit
of thy womb. Jesus.

1943
03:10:49.811 --> 03:10:53.780
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners.

1944
03:10:59.117 --> 03:11:00.589
(GUN FIRING)

1945
03:11:35.923 --> 03:11:39.694
Hey! Everybody. come on.
pay attention. Come here.

1946
03:11:39.729 --> 03:11:41.894
This is my friend
Carlo Rizzi.

1947
03:11:41.929 --> 03:11:44.765
My brother Fredo. Oh.
you know my brother Fredo.
Sure.

1948
03:11:44.800 --> 03:11:46.899
This is my
stepbrother Tom.

1949
03:11:46.934 --> 03:11:49.638
and that's
his girl Theresa.

1950
03:11:49.673 --> 03:11:51.574
This cute little thing
over here is my
sister Connie

1951
03:11:51.609 --> 03:11:52.971
I was tellin' you
about. huh?

1952
03:11:53.006 --> 03:11:55.710
Say hello to Carlo.
He's good-looking.
isn't he?

1953
03:11:55.745 --> 03:11:57.745
Yes.
(CHUCKLING)

1954
03:11:57.780 --> 03:12:00.176
Oh. that droopy thing
over there.
that's my brother Mike.

1955
03:12:00.211 --> 03:12:02.178
We call him Joe College.

1956
03:12:02.213 --> 03:12:04.180
Go on. Sit down.
Go ahead.

1957
03:12:04.215 --> 03:12:06.182
Talk to each other.
Sit down.

1958
03:12:06.217 --> 03:12:08.151
Hey. Mr. Einstein...

1959
03:12:08.186 --> 03:12:10.186
(CHATTERING)

1960
03:12:11.827 --> 03:12:12.892
Here's the cake.

1961
03:12:12.927 --> 03:12:14.355
Hey. Sally.
get in here!

1962
03:12:14.390 --> 03:12:16.863
I was scared.
Come on.

1963
03:12:16.898 --> 03:12:18.766
Where's your father?

1964
03:12:18.801 --> 03:12:20.801
Took him on
a wild goose chase.
Christmas shopping.

1965
03:12:20.836 --> 03:12:22.264
Let's see that thing.

1966
03:12:23.773 --> 03:12:24.871
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

1967
03:12:24.906 --> 03:12:26.741
Oh. honey.
that's nice. huh!

1968
03:12:26.776 --> 03:12:28.204
Should I put
the candles on now?

1969
03:12:28.239 --> 03:12:31.845
Yeah. Go on.
You help her. eh. Carlo.
Sure.

1970
03:12:31.880 --> 03:12:33.242
Hey. what is that? Rum?

1971
03:12:33.277 --> 03:12:35.013
Yeah.

1972
03:12:39.987 --> 03:12:43.318
Sonny. come on.
don't touch the antipasto
until Pop sees it.

1973
03:12:43.353 --> 03:12:44.858
He's not ugly...

1974
03:12:51.735 --> 03:12:53.867
I say. what do you think
of the nerve of
them Japs. huh?

1975
03:12:53.902 --> 03:12:55.330
Them slanty
eyed bastards. huh?

1976
03:12:55.365 --> 03:12:57.904
Dropping bombs
in our own backyard
on Pop's birthday.

1977
03:12:57.939 --> 03:12:59.400
They didn't know
it was Pop's birthday.

1978
03:12:59.435 --> 03:13:01.336
They didn't know
it was Pop's... (SCOFFS)

1979
03:13:01.371 --> 03:13:04.009
We should have expected it
after the oil embargo.

1980
03:13:04.044 --> 03:13:05.747
Expected?
Expected or not.

1981
03:13:05.782 --> 03:13:07.276
they've got no right
dropping bombs!

1982
03:13:07.311 --> 03:13:08.981
Are you a Jap-lover
or something.
you on their side?

1983
03:13:09.016 --> 03:13:11.148
I understand
30.000 men enlisted
this morning.

1984
03:13:11.183 --> 03:13:12.820
Bunch of saps...

1985
03:13:12.855 --> 03:13:14.690
Why are they
saps?

1986
03:13:14.725 --> 03:13:16.956
Honey. come on.
we don't have to
talk about the war.

1987
03:13:16.991 --> 03:13:19.156
Hey. you talk
to Carlo. all right?

1988
03:13:21.193 --> 03:13:24.700
Only saps because they risk
their lives for strangers.

1989
03:13:24.735 --> 03:13:26.163
Oh. that's Pop talking.

1990
03:13:26.198 --> 03:13:28.363
SONNY: You're goddamn right.
that's Pop talking!

1991
03:13:28.398 --> 03:13:30.299
They risk their lives
for their country.

1992
03:13:30.334 --> 03:13:32.202
Country ain't
your blood.
Remember that.

1993
03:13:32.237 --> 03:13:34.237
I don't feel that way.
SONNY: I don't feel that way.

1994
03:13:34.272 --> 03:13:36.074
Well. if you don't
feel like that.

1995
03:13:36.109 --> 03:13:38.142
why don't you
just quit college
and join the army!

1996
03:13:38.177 --> 03:13:39.275
I did.

1997
03:13:40.410 --> 03:13:42.179
I've enlisted
in the Marines.

1998
03:13:46.053 --> 03:13:48.086
Mike. why didn't you
come to us?

1999
03:13:48.121 --> 03:13:49.285
What do you mean?

2000
03:13:49.320 --> 03:13:51.056
Pop had to pull
a lot of strings

2001
03:13:51.091 --> 03:13:52.189
to get you a deferment.

2002
03:13:52.224 --> 03:13:54.257
I didn't ask
for it.

2003
03:13:54.292 --> 03:13:55.797
I didn't ask
for deferment.
I didn't want it.

2004
03:13:57.460 --> 03:13:58.998
Come on. come on!
Knock it off!

2005
03:13:59.033 --> 03:14:00.131
Come on. hey. Sonny.

2006
03:14:00.166 --> 03:14:01.429
Punk!
Sonny.

2007
03:14:01.464 --> 03:14:03.101
Sonny. Sonny. sit.
No. no. you go on.

2008
03:14:03.136 --> 03:14:04.201
Sit... Sit down.

2009
03:14:06.942 --> 03:14:10.075
Mommy. Daddy's
fighting again!

2010
03:14:10.110 --> 03:14:11.714
(KIDS LAUGHING)

2011
03:14:13.443 --> 03:14:15.278
Go and show Carlo
the tree.

2012
03:14:17.788 --> 03:14:19.117
(GIRL CHATTERING)

2013
03:14:26.489 --> 03:14:28.192
Nice.

2014
03:14:30.031 --> 03:14:32.097
Nice.

2015
03:14:32.132 --> 03:14:34.770
Break your
father's heart
on his birthday.

2016
03:14:35.971 --> 03:14:38.807
That's swell. Mike.
Congratulations.

2017
03:14:38.842 --> 03:14:41.040
That's right. encourage
him!

2018
03:14:41.075 --> 03:14:43.108
Go on.
Get me a drink.

2019
03:14:43.143 --> 03:14:44.373
Go on!

2020
03:14:47.543 --> 03:14:51.182
You don't understand.
Your father has plans for you.

2021
03:14:51.217 --> 03:14:55.417
Many times
he and I have talked
about your future.

2022
03:14:57.256 --> 03:14:59.025
You've talked to my father
about my future?

2023
03:15:02.327 --> 03:15:03.832
My future.

2024
03:15:03.867 --> 03:15:06.835
Mikey. he has
high hopes for you.

2025
03:15:06.870 --> 03:15:09.398
I have my own plans
for my future.

2026
03:15:09.433 --> 03:15:11.202
Did you go to college
to get stupid?

2027
03:15:11.237 --> 03:15:12.302
You're really stupid.

2028
03:15:12.337 --> 03:15:14.304
He's here! Come on!

2029
03:15:16.209 --> 03:15:17.406
Come on. Come on.

2030
03:15:20.444 --> 03:15:21.883
Stupid!

2031
03:15:38.495 --> 03:15:39.802
(DOOR OPENING)

2032
03:15:39.837 --> 03:15:42.134
ALL: Surprise!

2033
03:15:45.205 --> 03:15:47.073
ALL:
<i>♪ For he's</i>
<i>a jolly good fellow</i>

2034
03:15:47.108 --> 03:15:51.011
<i>♪ For he's</i>
<i>a jolly good fellow</i>

2035
03:15:51.046 --> 03:15:54.916
<i>♪ That nobody can deny</i>
<i>Nobody can deny... ♪</i>
